title: The Rose, the Fire, and the Woman
author: juan
text: they are all beautiful things.  they all bloom from the ground,  ready to brighten up your day.  how itâ’s done,  iâ’ll never know,  but i appreciate it.   the rose,  the fire and the woman.  they can all be deadly,  each more than the last.  one will make you bleed,  while the other will leave you burned.  but it is only the last one that will last the rest of your life.   the rose,  the fire and the woman.  each one requires plenty of care.  no amount of scolding will change the way they are.  they are that way by nature,  and really there is no better way.   the rose,  the fire and the woman.  if you truly love them,  though,  you will leave it be.  whether it is to grow,  to die,  or simply to be free.  itâ’s just the way it is,  and the way it should be.

title: Heartbreak
author: julia
text: the air turned sticky in the room.  sunlight careening through the window ricocheted and fell onto the floor.  she was close.   i could feel her  steps,  pounding up stairs  like drums before the attack.   door swung open and it began.  jagged words precisely aimed,   emotions hissed,  angrier than a cat trapped:  disappointment,   disapproval,  discontent,  disbelief.  these were strange sounds,  alien as the screech of the bus at dawn.     the words stopped and she departed.  but the emotions lingered,   filling the room with an acrid haze.  the bitter sting hung in the air,  replaying like a stuck cd,  wearing a hole in my heart.

title: Poetry
author: julitza
text: what is poetry? poetry is a medium for the artistic mind of writers.  it is a way of free expression.  to publish your own emotions,  though not always fully appreciated.  poetry is a portal into your very soul.  free for people to interpret its meaning,  but only for you to know the true purpose behind it.  it is where your innermost thoughts are let out using only a pen and paper.  to me,  poetry is the thing that brings me joy.  a chance to use my creativity and create something beautiful.  a way to vent my feelings without fear of being dismissed or scorned.  to me,  poetry is my life.

title: Love Thy Best Friend
author: kacey
text: rejection is the biggest infection in this heart of mine,  it seems my stars in the darkness will never align.  your lust and confusion in one bittersweet kiss,  i break my own heart in moments of bliss.  i think of the time when you said i was perfection,  and take it to the heart like a poisonous injection.  your desire and taste crash onto my lips,  then your eyes black out like an enthralled eclipse.  you obtain those feelings that make the heart sore,  in my soul so softly you whisper no more.  i swallow your excuses like a straight shot of whiskey,  i make a wish on your eyes hoping that youâ’ll miss me.  a girl canâ’t settle for your heart wrenching teasinâ’ she wants your emotions not your logic and reason.  maybe you will listen,  maybe i am crazy,  maybe i will wake up in a world not hazy.  i just want to know how your heart is dealing,  it might be classified as a tenuous dam of feeling.  you were once bruised and your heart is now tattered,  see what i see and know you are no longer battered.  meet me half way and we can walk without end,  let us set fire to this crusade and love thy best friend.

title: Unfinished

text: i'd hold the stars for you  in the palms  of my clumsy  hands.  they'd  burn a hollow hole through  the crevices  of each line that runs along my individual fingertips.    i built my walls up so high but you climbed the  tallest mountain   to tear them down.  you made me want see the world the same way i remember seeing you.    you painted me to fit  into in the museum  that is your head.  i wouldn't stay for long,  just hanging from the beige painted walls,  you'd sell me for millions.    i'm saying goodbye to the person i  became before you.  i fell into the palm  of your hands as easily as you fell into another.  i'm  better than i was before.    you and i,  we aren't alike you were a finished  home and i was just being built.   i deserve someone who looks at me the same way  that i looked at you.

title: Van Gogh
author: katie
text: my horoscope says i'm gonna die today.  i'm gonna kick the bucket after hitting the hay.  and in the morning while the world's still gray,  i'll sit beside myself in the bed where i once layed.   i'll have a conversation  with whoever wants to hear.  we'll talk about the traffic and polluted atmosphere.  we'll talk so fast we'll sound just like two texan auctioneers.  we'll ponder 'bout van gogh and that missing bit of ear.   this stranger's words are carved from the pain of blaphemy.  he was poisoned when we made him drink from the cup of cruelty.  how unfortunate that it took me until my eulogy to realize he is my god and not my enemy.

title: Journey Through My Eyes
author: kelecia
text: we woke up early this morning,   and things went on as usual.   mama got up before the sun,  and pa and the other men and little men in the village went off on a hunting trip,  in hopes of bringing back meat for dinner.    today is the day i become a woman,  today i turn 16,  today i wear my beads,  finally.  iâ’ve been making them for months ever since the arrangement was made.   dafari seems to grow taller every day,  his muscles are strong,  his shoulders broad.  i hurry through my chores,  just so i can go watch  him return from the forest with the other hunters.  satisfied,  i return to the land that would soon be our own,  and our childrenâ’s.    later the sun sets and the moon comes out,  we are eating when we first hear it,  was that a scream? our drummers cease,  as does the eating and the conversation.  it becomes clear… a shrill cry for help,  the drums go off again but this time it is the drumming sounds of danger.   they bring us to the ocean,   like animals we are packed inside their great canoe.  the voyage last forever,  people die beside me! people die in front of me! it stinks! its dark,  no way to tell what time of the day it is,  wrapped in the blanket of feces and the decaying odor of my people.   somehow i survive the journey…but for what? i am in a field that very same day the crop is soft and white the field is vast and seems never ending.   i have to keep working so i wonâ’t be whipped  that tearing away of flesh and the screaming from pain what did i do wrong? why am i here?  who are these people?  where is my family?  who am i?  i am a young woman,  marching down the streets of alabama,  with my brothers and sisters,  lead on by the footprints of martin luther king.  who am i?  i am an african-american male,  standing in line to vote-a sacred right reached through tears,  and blood,  and lives.   my pride suddenly becomes drenched from the powerful  fire hoses that knock me off my feet.   i get back up.   i do not throw punches.   i use all my energy to get inside.   i vote.  who am i?  i am a student listening to the derogatory speeches  of adults and students alike.  saying,  â“go back where you came from. â” but youâ’re the ones who brought me here.   barking at me as i walk through the doors of little rockâ’s central high school.   four years of stress,  four years of struggle,  four years of being here and not fitting in.   standing out like a sore thumb.  who am i?  i am a junior in high school in the year 2013.  i see first generation college students going to college for free.  i see sports prodigyâ’s getting full-ride scholarships.  yet… i see my people affiliating themselves with gangs,  refusing to go to class,  disrespecting their elders,  who are you?  you are the descendant of great african kings,  you are derived from the speeches of martin luther king,  â“i have a dream that my four children will one day live in a nation where they will not be judged by the color of their skin but by the content of their character. â” who am i?  i am rising above the oppression,   i will not allow myself to fail,  i am flying,  because i am no longer caged! i am young.   i am proud.   i am black.   i am free.

title: My Fear
author: kelsey
text: the throaty rumble                         overhead.  the ghostly song of those long dead.  the aching throb within my head.  i do not fear.   the tang of chains that bind me tight.  the curtain of dark that shuts out light.  the outcome of a deadly fight.  i do not fear.   the howling moan and glowing eyes.  the starless night with pitch-black skies.  the shriek of pain when someone dies.  i do not fear.   the hard cold whip to be alone.  with its silent  frightful tone.  the painful loss of my own.  this i fear.

title: The List
author: kelsie
text: i fear everything and nothing.  iâ’m afraid you will hate me for all the right reasons and heâ’ll like me for all the wrong ones.  iâ’m afraid of all the secrets iâ’m still too young to know and everything i donâ’t know yet.  so i end up listening anyway knowing iâ’ll regret it later,  because once something is learned it cannot be unlearned.  there are things in this world that no one should have to know.  i am afraid of my body.  how it works,  how itâ’s changing,  and how that changes everything else.  i want to be noticed yet uncomfortable when i am.  i walk by a group of boys and try to shrink smaller and grow taller at the same time.  thereâ’s a war inside me.  i am afraid of the choices and desires and all the wrong things i want and the right things i donâ’t.  i want to go with the flow but iâ’m troubled by my conscience.  iâ’m afraid that if i follow you iâ’ll lose me but if i choose me iâ’ll lose you.  iâ’m afraid of my strengths and i hate my weaknesses.  i donâ’t know what you want from me and iâ’m not sure how to be me.  i am confusion.  i am afraid of your thoughts,  your opinions,  your gossip.  as much as i donâ’t want to,  i care.  i am afraid that when i look at you i will find the worst of me and never the best of you and that means iâ’ll never recognize the best of myself.  i am afraid of all the mistakes i will make and i grow more unsure,  mistrusting,  and cautious of myself.   i know iâ’m the only one holding me back.  my fear holds me back from becoming me.  how can you hate me if you donâ’t know me?  because iâ’m just now getting to know myself.  iâ’m afraid of the pain and anger i allow you to cause me.   i am more afraid of the desire to hurt you back.  iâ’m afraid that no one else has the answers for me and i will never find my own.   iâ’m afraid youâ’re all better actors than me and the cost of becoming a better actor myself.  i am afraid i feel everything sometimes and then nothing at all.  iâ’m afraid of the pressure put on me to be this and not that,  to do this but never that,  how to talk,  look,  what friends to have,  and what boys to date.   i fear everything and nothing.

title: The conundrum of love
author: kristen
text: life so sweet,  time so short.   how can i show affection of a sort?  how can one describe their passion?  is it something natural or just modern fashion?  from first kiss to last,   my love for you is eternal to the past.    the love we share is simple at first glance,   ever since we met,  i now seize every chance.   to a distant star between nothing and infinity,   stay within the boundaries of serenity with me.   let the flame remain un-extinguished and soar,   permit me to love you,  kiss you,  cherish you forever more.    confusion impurifies my soul,  tears me at the seams,   when i know i should exist only with the prince of my dreams.   the conundrum of a sociology,  the paradox of philosophy,   is really quite a simple solution,  discovered easily.   for if your love is moral,  pure and true,   then i infer that i am always to be with you.    the love that escalates everyday,   can no longer be contained,  but is difficult to be expressed in any way.   if my beloved is hurt,  i feel double his pain,   if it was by my hand or heart,  hysteria has illed my brain.   for to do such an idiotic and hideous action,   makes my own metacognition murky right down to every junction.    but with every tender and passionate kiss we share,   it shows how much you care.   for i feel like a clod,  an oaf,  an inferior being,   to try to deny the love,  the passion,  burning and all seeing.   into the wee hours of the morn',   my body is wasted,  but my heart is reborn.    love me forever more and until  i shed this form of the living to a dimension where i shall lie still.   from the sweet taste of your lips,  the fragrance of your hair,   nothing in this world,  could ever compare.   for if your heart chills,  aches,  or throbs,   the tears i shed for my beloved are whaling sobs.    my heart aches and forcefully preserves the torture of parting.    this swills the balance,  creating and enmity; darker,   to be presented with emotional and physical pleasure may suffice,  and feels more enthralling twice!  however,  where i do stand if i am traveling with a faulty compass?  to the extent of where shall our hearts meet on this road of glass.    my deepest desire is to kiss you goodnight,   and whisper in your ear,  ''i love you, '' with no more reverence or plight.  to serenade you in bilingual romance,   is to ricochet to the stars in a cosmic dance.   angels above envy me for you,  my good fortune,  for it is impossible to find such another entity of your punctuality and conception.    with lips so sweet and skin too tender,  it's no wonder my heart did surrender.  to you your name might be brian; independence's teacher,   but,  you,  to me are my perfect sole prince.   when the storm retreats and the sun begins to shine,   i am reminded how lucky i am that you're mine.    space is the final frontier into the heavens,  through the skies,   but,  it's obvious those astronomers never saw your beautiful brown eyes.   how fate must despise us.  how he must obsess.   every time we are happy with a gentle caress.   but,  despite such adversities,  by and by,  through and through,   my heart,  body,  mind,  and soul shall always belong to you.

title: I Miss You

title: Do You Recognize Freedom?
author: kristina
text: do you know the faces of the soldiers who have died so you have freedom to your left  and justice on your right side?  can you believe all the foreign lies who promised us help and then never supplied?  do you remember when our country bled,  they stole our spirits and replaced them with fear instead?  have you tried counting our fallen troops who brought freedom to our land so thereâ’s a flag you can salute?  can you read all the signs held by the protestors who support the troops but donâ’t support what theyâ’re dying for?  do you believe  all of the celebrities for cursing our leader yet wanting countless liberties?  do you remember when our country was born it was then the people appreciated just what weâ’re fighting for.   do know you just how this war will end will we still be a country extending a friendly hand?  do you wander? just how many will die so that we can be free and hold our heads high  do you ever dream about the troops over there who are sleeping in mud so that justice may prevail?  can you understand the blood that is shed so that we can stand tall with the flag waving freely above our heads?  do you understand the reason we wonâ’t give in  to a man  who is killing his own citizens?  america,  this is freedoms home this is why we fight to call it our own america,  where tears are shed for those who wander looking for  freedoms bed.   america,  this is where we have the right to pray for our troops with all of our might.   america,  you stand tall leading the way  for those who toil  for freedoms hall.

title: Dependent Love

text: sand castles and crashing waves and little grains of sand sneaking between your toes mountains and canyons and the smell of a campfire lighting up the area with the monotone crackling our favorite places are a metaphor for our life our view our hopes and dreams and most importantly an insight at love  is your love a monument you slowly built up that just keeps getting knocked down is your love strong and then weak because the little light in your darkness pulls and pushed you away when it wants to    or is your love  undestroyable or so it seems until one by one a little part of you starts to break off and crash until it's just little pebbles pebbles pebbles trust  gets shaken down from the power of lies crash hope breaks away until it's just dust floating in the air crash your dreams  little trails created by love some rockier than others some smooth  some taken over by the manipulation of others  others taking your dreams away to fulfill their own crash  along with the little light in your darkness warms you and gives a sense of protection against the coldness surrounded by the dark bareness until it burns and burns burns everything around you  even the tops of the mountains to the bottom of the ocean depend on something to keep them on track don't beat yourself for depending on someone who you know can ruin everything you've ever known whenever they want build yourself up for taking the risk   which love is your love

title: Where I Belong
author: liezl
text: home is playing music as loud as i desire every sound of strum echoing through the hallways and reaching through each room,   the melody of each key bouncing off the walls like an easy game of pinball,  a strong,  calming rush running inside me as if witnessing an ocean wave when hitting pitch perfect.    home is snuggling with visions of fantasies and dreams through a book flipping through the pages until my eyes feel heavy,  no longer able to keep them open,    millions of words transforming into a long movie in my head,  losing track of time,   getting too caught up in different charactersâ’ stories,  feeling their emotion and forgetting about reality.    home is being comfortable and not having to impress anyone where a bare face is flawless and perfect,  and m. a. c is not allowed to come over,   my loose,  messy bun falling apart after about 3 minutes of putting it up,   not caring if the colors of my tee and sweats arenâ’t completely matching.    home is letting out emotions any way i want crying on my pillow and waking up to baggy eyes,  looking like i havenâ’t slept in days,   slamming doors to keep out everything else while the walls shake from frustration,   rambling on to my best friend releasing all my bottled up feelings.    home is mixes of aromas throughout the air steaming white rice from my grandmotherâ’s soft palms fills the kitchen,   jasmine green tea dad bought specially for me in my hands still too hot to drink,   holding my breath on saturdays not wanting to inhale the windex momâ’s using to clean.    home is where i belong.

title: THE GIRL IN THE FISH BOWL
author: lyla
text: a girl, in the middle of her youth,  still too young to be too sure,  what she is and whats in store,  she feels jus like a lilttle fish,  in a bowl ,  sometimes clear and sometimes misty ,  this girl she always feels confused,  trapped ,  helpless and bemused,   this girl jus as she presses her head,   against the glass of the bowl,  she feels that the goldfish ,  and her share a thought,  a way of life and  she stares,  as she feels they make a pair,  sometimes she watches as the cat jumps , right in tryin to make his catch,  the poor little fish is so scared ,  swimming around trying to find a way out  hanging on for sweet life,  and she thinks,  the similarities just never end.  for bad times they come and go,  just as she pushes the cat away from the bowl,  she realizes there is a time every , problem just has to end.     the water is jus like her life ,  hot and cold warm n nice,  sometimes it feels like ,  the bowl is just too small ,  and she wishes to be freed from it all.  for when the cold and mist come along,  her life seems way too long.   then she wishes that it would end ,  jus so that shed be helpless no more,  the sun comes out darkness fades away,  again she thinks of how she pushed the cat away,  every problem will be solved,  even though sometimes she feels the bowls too small,  and wishes that her life would end,  hope is always greater then despair,  and she knows this phase will definately end.

title: MY REFLECTION

text: when i see my reflection in a mirror  i feel content but also bewildered i wonder what made me look like so  and what lies ahead and whats in store i imagine things both good and bad sometimes i feel lonely n very sad sometimes i smile content with what i have but most of the time i seem to think what is it that i need to bring  to make myself important in this world and make a diffence and be heard  i feel sometimes that i am like a little spider trying its best to climb a high rise wall meeting obstacles on its way  crossing some ,  and using the miracle of time to let the others pass  i sometimes feel frightened that it may never reach the top  and if so then it will drop right down n far below  never then will it rise again   i may not die in my physical being but my whole life will crumble down to small pieces and bring many frowns on the face of my family and friends as i could not reach the height that was truly ment for me.

title: My Wish
author: lynzie
text: i herd some bad news today,  something that left me with a scare,  today i found out my cousin has leukemia; it became my biggest fear.   i cry myself to sleep at night trying not to ask god why? how could this be real? i wish it were a lie  i know i have to be strong,  and my prayers are always said,  but the question is: does anyone really hear me when iâ’m lying there in bed?  when i go to sleep at night i wish this horrible nightmare would just go away but itâ’s so real and for some reason this leukemia inside you wants to stay.   i wish i could just hold you and take away every ounce of your pain  i sit here trying to be strong for you but my tears fall like rain  i remember all the fun times we used to share i miss all those laughs and hugs that showed how much you care.   i remember the long drives we would take,  driving down dirt roads jamming out to are favorite songs.  i remember all the times you would yell at me pointing out all my little wrongs.   you were like my big brother billy,  the closest one i had i feel so lost,  so hurt and angry i wish i werenâ’t this sad.   what really hurts me most is knowing your suffering and there is nothing i can do.  i am here and you are there,  i wish i wasnâ’t so many miles apart from you…  all this time i lost with you,  all the letters i did not write and now itâ’s really haunting me please donâ’t leave my sight…  i have so many questions so many thoughts,  i just want someone to tell me everything is ok; iâ’m slowly losing grip i feel like iâ’ve lost my way.   sometimes i wonder why god does such things to us knowing it brings us pain.  itâ’s me against the world; i put on a happy face trying to stay sane.   i lay here wondering how my little billy might feel? hoping and praying that soon my cousin will heal  billy is getting sicker; i ask myself is he going to make it through this? lord please make him better this is my one and only wish!

title: The Metropolis
author: mahir
text: staring out of the window,  what do i perceive?  vast fields and meadows,  birds on mango trees.   a cow grazes here and there,  munching on the grass,  sheep and goat and buffalo,  traverse the landmass.    staring out of the window,  what do i perceive?  tall buildings of concrete,  dull and grey.   a car honks here and there,  a motor whizzes past,   and if i happen to see a tree,  it leaves me aghast.    staring out of the window,  what do i perceive? the destruction of my town and the form of a city.  instead of cart and bull,  i see a motor car,   what has happened to my town,  i donâ’t know who to ask.    staring out of the window,  what do i perceive?  with broken heart and watery eyes the dreaded metropolis.   i long for fields and yearn for trees,  but none can i find,  the only thing i have today,  is smoke in my eyes.

title: Brief Burning Moment
author: mary
text: i stand on the sidewalk,  watching the world pass by  in slow motion.   i gaze at the towering building,  mesmerized by the  raging fire.   unable to move my eyes,  they burned from the smoke that  flooded the air.   paralyzed by the silhouettes,  all running crazily in place crazed and confused.   whereâ’s my baby! screamed a woman,  where she came from i donâ’t know.   just another silhouette in a window.   the rain pours down,  yet i donâ’t move.  i still stand there  just staring.   the black mysterious figures against the angry hues,  the smell of death  diffuses in the air.   in one window i see the silhouettes of a man and a woman.  he grabs her hand and  they jump.   ahhhh! her high-pitched cry rang out into the smoky darkness.  her shriek rang  repeatedly  they hit the pavement and i shake in terror.  as they hit,  a blood red mist  fills the air   the silhouettes keep falling from windows,  like the tears falling from my eyes  itâ’s the beginning of the end.   the sounds of sirens flood my ears.  the flashing red lights pierce the darkness.   men flood out of the long red vehicles.  yelling and shouting that makes my head spin.   hurry! my wife ainâ’t breathinâ’.  a man yells.  he is on the eighth floor.  she wonâ’t make it.   one of the firefighters ran out with a man on his shoulder.  the man is on fire,  his flesh burning.   boom! half of the first floor bursts.  bits of bricks and bodies splatter the street.   thud.  i hit the ground.  trampled by a gathering of people.  i blink.   once i regain my posture.  i look down to see that i am covered in ash and blood.   my once white shirt is now blood stained.  my hair wet from both rain and splatter,  clings to me.   i have witnessed something terrorizing,  something that will never leave my mind.  it will haunt me.   that brief burning moment.

title: My Old, Beloved School

text: as i sit in front of this computer,  like working with a tutor,  i think back on days of old,  when during winter,  i'd get cold.   that don't happen any more.  after lunch,  i walk through no door.  up the stairs i go,  thinking of days long ago.  wanting to feel chilled down to my core.   i speak of my school of old.  where many a lesson was told.  back with my classmates.  back with the debates.  i was the clay and the school was the mold.   but here i am now.  no classmates or recess.  the only friend i have is my girlfriend jess.   i like my new school,  don't get me wrong.  i think it's kinda' cool.  but to my old school,   my heart will always belong.

title: Sky
author: michael
text: how far,  how close,  doesnâ’t matter; how many,  how few,  doesnâ’t neither; for every humanity at each corner of our realm he is shared.  for he is the spiritual medium in which souls will flow; and the sign of covenant our god endlessly put on his tearful face of sorrow.  â“loneliness is impossible!â” shouts the roof of all,  â“i cover you,  the ashamed and the proud,  the frightened and the cheerful,  and the wicked being that bowed and with me,  shared a salvation look,  warm and cool.   for i was born to clothe you with more,  for my brother,  the endless time and for my father,  he created me for i am yours,  as you are mine.

title: Triune
author: michael
text: as a blink of an eye,   separating us from everlasting sleep and eternal sight,   both fruitless as my two faces that never die,   i contrast darkness and light.   with no power of choosing sides,   i find myself clothed with either one,  then the other  like a coin tossed,  flipping,  never returns but glides.   confusion and profitless   are a maze that my two faces canâ’t get a way from  and away from each other but are effortless;  awaiting for me to bear only one of them,  as i roam;  but in vain,  remembering that i wish i could.   after many thoughtful nights,   dawn rose,  with a question i longed for:  â“what about you,  the third of you?  the one with a choice.   to be neither of them,  to get through,   with a command from your voice.   as three of you donâ’t need those two to be oneself;  to be yourself.   as for the coin,   forbid it from dwelling in disorientated spaces,   reach it and make it land on neither faces. â”

title: Thread of life
author: michael
text: i stretch,  bridging your life with your neighborâ’s at a random edge of the furthest corner i shrink,  as a bottomless ocean of strife,  to let your fortunes cross,  and find each other.  i tangle,  but never break; for you,  to meet,  surely is as crucial as the worldâ’s fate constantly avoiding good,  as i am awake.  â‘red thread of destinyâ’,  i am called by myth,  not only have i tied your ankle to your faraway resident,  i bonded and forged a nation,  from you and with.  certainly fruitless will it be,  foretelling my being; consider me reticent.  but no worries friendless; now as you doubt,  someoneâ’s longing for you out there just for you.

title: Blue the Toad
author: michael
text: sammy walked outside one day.  a fine day it was in may.     she walked to the lake to skip a stone but soon realized,  she was alone  ''if only i could find a friend,  to come with me'',  she added then.   she then bent down to tie her shoe and saw a toad his name was blue  ''i am blue king of the toads,  and you are standing on my road. ''  ''i am sorry'',  said sammy dear ''i knew not that you were here. ''  ''don't apologize. '' he said with a frown then started crying,  and quite loud  ''what's the matter great king blue,  what did i say? what did i do?''  ''nothing,  nothing'',  he said with a sigh.  ''nobody comes here,  you can go by. ''  ''i'm off to skip a stone you see,  would you care to come with me?''  ''yes of course i'll go with you. '' ''it's your lucky day, '' thought blue.

title: Day and Night
author: natalie
text: twinkles of light dance in the night,   around the moon in majestic flight.   but down behind the seas the glide,   now it's time for darkness to hide.   for rainbows of pink and yellow rise,   and a new light shines over the tide.   as the sun floats over the day,   birds and children come out to play.   at dusk the fire sinks into the field,   while families turn in for their final meal.   a grey abyss creeps over the sky,   thunder and lightning across the night cry.   with flashes of anger and cracks of fury,   critters on the ground flee in a hurry.   the blanket of black stretches end to end,   until surely the light wakes us again.

title: Remberance day

title: God and His candle
author: rob
text: god help us home in the dark,  alone godâ’s light is out and no light shone -- the magnet coast is the devilâ’s voice pulling us home,  we have no choice.   beneath the terror and screams of splinters and shattering beams -- my last friend not god is whom i sail with in rocks and doom.   no holy lighthouse in sight no candle guides us tonight.  we falter in howls of glory and the sea devours our story.   the jagged foes rising from the sand  our wooden savior does not withstand -- the mast sinister with choice topples to halt the mortal voice.                                 the horizon rises and in death flows blue evil rules and faithâ’s hull goes.  for my friend and i the hourâ’s late and we sing not to god -- but to fate:   hand over a guitar my friend weâ’ll sing to brighten the end and iâ’ll pluck it to the beat of the waves drumming defeat.    and in the faded starlight we float  whitecaps mix the splintered boat forsaken and lost by divine eyes we mortals lose our unholy lives.

title: Wants and Wonder
author: rob
text: in the corner of my eye a wanting soul i think i spy silence bears our quiet chat -- i wonder if that is finally you.   yet i do not know you yet nor if our futures are the same so my desire is that just maybe  you are wondering about me too.   turning to better look at you --  i stare at you staring back at me.  but thatâ’s not loving in your eyes and that smile is just to be polite.   then love and company comes and sits all close beside you  and we turn away so quickly that my envy takes a pause.   but soon i move to hating and myself the worst of all  for no one wants to wonder how i love and am and all.

title: The Ultimate Swim
author: rob
text: she drops her shoes in the sand and frees her golden hair and takes a timorous breath as she walks into the sea.   she slides her feet through the foam and wades into the setting sun and smiles with forlorn eyes at every fishâ’s lament.   she raises her right hand to wave that last goodbye and boards the looming swell and descends into the depths to advance her timeless peace.

title: Lies a Heart
author: ryan
text: in every man lies a heart.   confused and troubled when they start.   though they fail and fall down.   they always have the strength to get off the ground.     pushing your body through the pain.    the only thing you get is gain.   character is built the journey begins.   then all of a sudden it all ends.     the path to success is crooked and troubled.   almost as if the path is doubled.    once at the end and doomed for success.   the time is now,  no time for rest.     the light you hold in your hand.   extinguishes darkness to reveal the land.   so wherever you are in the journey of life.   your path is lit,  not gloomy,  but bright.    all of a sudden,  all is gone.   and then you hear a beat-a beat to words.   everything becomes clear. . . why?  in every man lies a heart.   confused and troubled when they start.

title: Love is blind

text: i do not believe in love because love has blinded the oneâ’s i love most.  therefore love is blind there is no other way to put it.  but we must learn to live and love life like it is our deepest treasure of all.   even if i hate so much i must agree with the facts of life.  but in all my heart i still truly will always love thee.  for you have taken my heart with such affectionate words of emotion.  but you did not say any of them until i was gone out of the picture.  even now that i am gone i now with all my heart that you did truly love me.   so i give you my love but with such pain of grief.  i feel as though i will never know the true meaning of love until i loose it forever i love thee with all my heart.

title: Hello. Is it dark?
author: sarah
text: hello.  is it dark?  i cannot tell as i can only peer in through the outside  you are deeper down than i will ever understand i say i can find help for you  i will get you out of the well but i donâ’t.  and for that i am sorry.  it is impossible,  i think,  for me to get you out there is no ladder long enough to reach you hello.  is it dark?  i can only ask you questions,   though i know i will not get the full answers because you are so deep in that well so very deep that i no longer know who you are  your voice,  the words you expel are just a faã§ade  i canâ’t possibly see all the way in  and so i turn my head.    \tand for that,  i am sorry.   but can you blame me?  if i try to help you,  if i travel deep into your well i can accidentally fall in  and i do not want that to happen or if i donâ’t fall in,  you could fall deeper  but if i only peer in,  i am not responsible.  i remember when you would ask me for your help when we both drowned in your tears \tbut those tears were not the rain you had hoped would save you  you tried to drag me in  you pulled and pulled,  but i resisted because i did not want to be responsible for the girl in the well  \tand for that,  i am sorry.   hello.  is it dark?  i ask because i want to know i want to know what you are going through  but you will never answer me because you can never fully explain the darkness \tunless you are in the well out of fear,  out of unknowing,  i walk away \tand for that,  i am sorry.   you are helpless,  scared,  you cannot see the brightness of the outside world and i am so fortunate that when i walk away,   even at night,  i am in the safety of the light.  i hope that sometimes i can help you forget that you are in the well and that jokes and hugs can suffice if only there was a way to knock down the walls around you  and remove you from your well but there isnâ’t so i pretend that your well is not even there \tand for that,  i am sorry.   hello? i know that it is dark.   darker than anything i hope to ever see  and i wish there was something else i could do  besides turning my head \tand for that,  i am sorry.   and even though i walk away from your well please know that  \tfor that,  i am sorry.

title: Butterflies Wings
author: savanna
text: a butterfly lands upon my knee and i treat it with great care,  i love its every moment,  but before long it is'nt there.    the butterfly flies around to see the beautiful place it's in,  but can't stay here much longer i knew this from within.   i cherish each moment it stays here and learn to love its shine,  gleaming from inside its wings,  i only wish that it was mine.   i know it's going to leave now,  and in my palm i hold so tight,  the life i had with this creature had let off such a beautiful light.   as i watch it slowly fly away a tear rolls down my cheek,  like the life made me feel stronger,  and like death,  has left me weak.

text: i walk in a room and all stare  like the sunrise i open your eyes glances from me make your heart stutter  my touches give you goose bumps i amaze you,  as my feet never hit the ground gliding by makes your heads turn i smile  confident  i dumbfound you,  as i speak my knowledge pours onto you  like the rain my words hit you like pellets of food,  food for the brain i will achieve donâ’t let my appearance fool you my mind is confident  i stand straight and tall like royalty sexy and slim like wine others who wish turn green my eyes brown changes to the sun all fascinated by my grace lake,  long hair streaming down ones who hate turn and frown i laugh  confident  people gather flabbergasted my posture is unique one tries to imitate my stance my two feet are firm onto the ground knee slightly bent one hand on my hip i stand perfectly still no need to move about  my body is confident  ones who whisper astonished brown skin glowing thick,  full lips  my arms sway back and forth hypnotizing ones who stare men bow as i pass through wishing they could be the one i walk confident  you cannot break the code to my heart thereâ’s know understanding to the key i wonâ’t block out though it isnâ’t easy to get in so many have tried and failed to poison my inner glow rejection is not an issue although,  acceptance is negativity is ignorant i stun you,  as you have never seen anything so deep  my soul is confident  legs,  long and smooth make you wonder  waist of pride a moment of my presence takes your breath away your eyes on me as i move jealous smirks roll off of my curved back i look  confident  strong eyes make you pay attention dress fits like heaven my head held high makes you shy step by step i wrap you into me i am  confident.

it's times when you feel like you are trapped in the very arems of a bad spirit
\n(but you're not) it's times when you feel like the presence of a ceased one is around (but you can't see them) it's times when you think that everybody has turned against you (but they didn't) it's times when you think that everybody hates you (but they don't) it's times when you feel like you are not free to fly (but you are) it's times when you feel like you are alone in this world (but you are not) it's times when you want to break down and cry for no reason. (but you don't because you are strong) it's times when you feel like you don't exist (but you do) it's times when you feel like you lost your loved ones. title: My Shrinking Violet
author: simeon
text: she was planted fifteen years ago she was given sun and room to grow and april showers washed her buds and she did not bloom,  a shock to us.   while other flowers grew and grew,  my violet was small and covered in dew she did not absorb the water drops that sat upon her purple tops.   then summer came and flowers shrunk they withered and wilted in the sun but my shrinking violet opened up and stretched her petals and grew up.   she was the most pretty of all in the garden against the old brick wall and even though she took some time this little violet is mine.   i wouldn't have another.

title: What is Love?
author: stacey
text: is love seeing stars in anotherâ’s eyes feeling safe in their arms smiling without meaning to smile caring without wanting to care being your best friend,  your passion needing to be near each other missing them when they just left anxious to hear their voice watching a movie without seeing the screen holding each other passionately hurting when they hurt burning when they cry listening when they speak dancing without knowing how to dance wanting their skin on yours feeling their body heat under yours feeling your blood boiling without being touched seeing their blood pool with every stroke of your hand watching as their cheeks turn from pink to deep red with every glance in their direction seeing them in your sleep hurting more than you ever have before if and when they leave you for the last time you never know that youâ’re in love until you see your life being fulfilled by this one person who makes every difference in the world people say love is just a figure of your imagination that may be the truth but you should never give up on the one love that makes your every dream come reality is all this love? who can know for sure what love truly is until you experience it your self?

title: They Don't Know
author: stephanie
text: all my life i was lonely and felt out of place,   my whole life not once did i ever feel safe.  now as i get older and the days pass by i slowly wish that i would die.  my love has faded and my souls grown cold,  but i know deep inside that i gotta stay bold.  every day i'm locked up in a place that don't help,  every night i lie down and feel my tears melt.  my family don't know about my every day pain,  they have no clue that i'm slowly goin insane.  my trust has gone low and my heart has grown weak,  nobody understands the depression i speak,  nobody sees the love that i seek.  i'm slowly dying in ways they don't know,  i'm slowly dying in ways i don't show.  with the minutes that pass my pain gets worse,  i feel my whole life is just one big curse.  my best friend disappeared with out a trace,  and my mother feels that i'm a disgrace.       i try and i try and get no results,    it's not my fault i act on impulse.  the pain in my heart cant top the pain in my soul,  every day i look into the mirror and  stare into eyes the color of coal.  i wish i could make you see the things i see,  i wish i could make you feel the things i feel,  at least this way you'll know that my pain is for             real.

title: Another roadside love

text: on a lonely seat sat the lonesome boy and a fair maiden did walked from there the guy just watched and never said a word  life was bleak,   but it did mean something to him now one day he smiled at her  she did replied his smile,  with a smile much more brighter than the light  after a month of passing smiles he finally found his voice inside and enough courage to talk to her and she listened as he spoke,   and he just talked some more. . .   after the 3 months just as friend,  he told her that he loved her   even more than one one can do,  and that he can be a lot better was it the starting of something great? or the another dream just shattered?  many nights did they spend together,  for many nights they were there and then the terror came no one knew whose fault it was,  but he knew that it was not his for sure  the time went by,  the girl got better the guy still lamented behind the girl moved on. .  but the guy was never  seen the fire in his heart was gone gone was his radiant smile  empty lays that lonely seat now no guy sits there and smiles no one knows where he is gone or what happened after this only a few may know that he still lives anything else is unknown it was nothing more than,  another roadside love

title: One-sided Lover
author: tanisha
text: as i look down walking the street,  i think about the next time we will ever meet.  in a lawn full of roses red,  why do these thoughts even come to my head?  there was once a time when i would say,  looking at you would make my day.  it was hard for me to stand tall,  for the more you'd talk,  the more i'd fall.   i then realized that i'd fallen in love with you,  i prayed to god to let this dream come true.  but never thought that those days would change,  and make everything seem so strange.   then came the days filled with tears,  i was surrounded with my own fears.  did you even feel the same for me,  or did you want to see my heart nailed to a tree?  then came a day when all this had to end,  things were so awkward,  i couldn't even make you my friend.  i had to move on,  had to let go,  or did you feel for me,  but didn't dare to show?  later on,  i found other fishes in the lake,  but my heart revived,  no one could make.  i felt like i was living a trick,  in which i owned the magic stick.   the gorgeous sunbeam just struck my face,  people admired it with eyes full of grace.  as i smiled and looked at all,  my eyes went to someone who had once made me fall.   you came up to me,  there was silence for a while,  the only thing that we did was look down and smile.  you looked at me and i looked at you,  something told me that this dream would now come true.   life has to go on,  with or without your dream,  we spoke for a while,  all i wanted to do was scream.  i said,  ''i'm fine.  yes,  i woke up one day with another name''.   but deep within,  i still feel the same. . .

text: and i was cast down from heaven unto fire and sulfur ,  into darkness for eternity beneath my feet,  i created ground to walk upon and for my wings,  i created air to soar upon and for my lips,  i created water to drink from and from my eyes,  i created light to see my prison and for my amusement,  i created man this is my domain and i will call it earth  and it is good.   and with this race of men will come great fortitude tyranny,  greed,  lust with these my powers will grow and a great time will come when i shall call upon the leaders of men to war within themselves.      and with this war my soldiers will emerge from the ashes of tyranny,  greed,  and lust and we will march through the gates of heaven and my soldiers will be great because their sins were greater  and i will claim my rightful place upon the throne and when the last of your gods  and angels are no more a new dawn will shine down upon great nothingness and i will rule this great void and  my sanctuary will be eternal so it is written so it shall be done.      genocide 1:1

title: My Beach
author: tori
text: lying on the beach with crashing waves upon the shore,  i feel the sun beaming heat down onto my skin.  the air is filled with the scent of fresh sea life,  tiny,  rippling sand dunes surround my towel.   lying on this beach i am completely serene,  all my worries seem to wash away with the current.  as i bask in this moment i wish to remain here always,  iâ’ve become one with nature.   lying on this beach i hear seagulls flying overhead,  theyâ’re calling me to return to myself.  suddenly,  reality hits,  my beach may be gone for now,  but it will endure in my heart forever.

title: Corn
author: trent
text: corn  corn,  starts from a tiny seed,  a miniscule,  little bead.  with help of a farmerâ’s toil,  it is placed in deep,  rich soil.   farmers pray without a doubt,   miniature green plants will sprout.  corn emerges from below,  time for fields of plants to grow.   height gained with water and sun,   to witness is really quite fun.  leaves and stalks turning visible,  but,  corn is not invincible.   drought or an animalâ’s bite,  roots and leaves lose their might.  too much water from the sky,   farmers will kiss their crop goodbye  with a small amount of luck,  the crop grows larger than a truck.   by the time autumn rolls around,  combines start to run the ground.   liquid gold flows from the fields,  farmers begin tallying yields.  kernels harvested,  stalks left alone,  through winter chilled to the bone.   the green tractors lay dormant,  and farmers wait in torment.   in spring it begins again,  forever corn we will defend.

title: Way out.
author: tsai
text: there it is.  there is what i want.  the blue sky is there, the white cloud is there.  but at the same time,  there is someone standing there,  who tried to stop me from looking at the blue sky.  who are you? who are you? ''i'm the dark. '', he said.  why do you try to stop me,  beat me,  and push me into the darkness? ''because this is what i want!'' i scream,  loudly and scared.  no! no! no! why me? why me? after one day,  two days,  three days. . . . . .  i hide myself,  into the dark.  afraid and cry,  all the time.  why me? why me?  why didn't he choose others? why all the bad things just happen to me? why me? why me? ''don't be afraid. '' a soft voice says suddenly.  i jump up,  look around the dark.  who are you? who are you? ''i am the light. '', she said.  why do you try to talk to me, say something warm to me,  and embrace me so softly? ''because this is what i want. '' i smile,  thankfully and happily.  thanks,  thanks,  thanks.  thanks for your warm.  and the dark disappear.  i look around,  find that i am standing at the top of the world; i touch the blue sky,  i hug the white clouds.  here it is.  here is what i want.

title: The Fruits of Death
author: umayr
text: the fruits of my future have told me everything,  my dreams have turned to me now.   they cry out in utter despair and agony,  questioning me,  not â“why?â” but â“how?â” because they do not understand either.   i lift my head up; long black bangs covering all put a miniscule portion of my once radiant face.  and i turn my head first,  to the right,  where the bright,  dense presence of a peach awaits my gaze.  and then i turn to the left,  where the red appleâ’s luminous texture reflects the surface of the imaginary sun,  and shines brightly.   they both scream at me the visions of what is to come.   first,  i see a pair of friends; their jolly smiles and their pearly white teeth make the peach denser.  and then,  i see them drifting away like pieces of wood on the crisp,  blue ocean surface.  and then,  i see them coming back,  their narrowed faces of anger consuming their being and everything around them,  and the apple begins to glow.  and then i see just one.   i see one of them,  his hand stained in blood,  walking away from other with the sinister grin of triumph plastered all over his maniacal face.   the apple begins to shine with a divine radiance,  and it is radiance that demands to be savored.   i look behind me,  now,  and the black background that i once knew changed before my eyes into a gleeful blue sky.  and i turn my head first,  to the left,  where the plain apple i once held glows in the light of a divine glory,  its beauty unparalleled.  and then,  i turn to the right,  where the peach is no longer present,  and i realize all too late that nothing had been resting upon my extended palm.   i have made my decision.   lifting the apple to my mouth,  i take an ever so negligible nibble from its blood-red skin,  expecting to be cloaked in its divine radiance.  but nothing happens.  so i wait,  \tand wait,  \t\t       and wait,  \t\t\t\tand wait.  but nothing happens.   \t\tand so i wait,  \t\t\t\tand wait.  but nothing happens.   \tand so i wait.   but nothing happens.   so i move forward,  my left hand,  coveting the sacred apple,  and my right hand,  stained in blood.   i walk away from the one i once called my friend,  clenching his bloodied garments tight in my right hand.   and i turn to the apple,  whose surface shines with praise,  joy,  and jubilance,  seeking its approval.   and then i wake up.   back in the flames of torture,  from which i was and from which i am.   and for the last time,  i see my friend,  standing above me; a peach in his right hand,  and my will in his left.   i mutter my last words of gratitude to him,  and tell him to covet that peach he holds in his right hand.   and he throws it down,  and i catch it,  in my right hand.    and the fruits of my future,  begin whispering among themselves,  once again,  trying to understand,  that dream.  that beginning.  that end.

title: Why people never get what they want?
author: vaibhav
text: as an infant laying in the arms of my mother,  never thought about things i got,  least bothered,  and now i ask the same question because i get haunt,   why people never get what they want?   took birth in january the time so old,  like the month,  my life too,  is cold.  like the cold winds would have swept the area when i took birth,   today the winds have submerged my life leaving no mirth.    the sky was beautiful,  a lovely blue,  but it changed rapidly the loved hue.  many colours it changed but i still don't know,  does it even got a true one to show?  like a blind man knows little where he's heading to,   a stick given makes him find his way new.   more than the blind man,  i was in darkness too,   until i found the stick but did it found me too.    i just wanted my life to hold me together,   we should gather all the happiness together.  but my life wasn't ready to let me live at that time,   ''it's ok,  it's fine'',  i said, but i was dying.    i loved my life so bad,  but it got so badly mad.   i guess i deserve all the pain i had,   but was i that bad?  i don't know when i'll have my querie dead,   will i have to take it to my death bed.   but every night this question does haunt,   why people never get what they want?

title: Valkyrie
author: yifei
text: the midday sun was shining bright,  above the wooded mountain heights; leaves and blossoms gaily sheen,  in rolling waves of emerald green.  southward came the summer breeze,  the oak leaves fluster,  and then cease; chirps and flutters,  the ear could heed,  sparrows skimming the canopy.  through the foliage,  the lustrous light,  shed from that cloudless august sky; crowns the copse with shining hues,  of lincoln green and peacock blue.  in which refuge made the timid fawn,  as its mother graze the lawn; another doe,  but too young to breed,  with tender limbs,  lie calm asleep.  her couch was the river grass,  moist with dew and gleams like glass; soft as fur every trembling blade,  as the stream,  it sweeps the glade.  reflects the rose's crimson glow,  or the hawthorn petals pale as snow; with feign piety the mantis pray,  'neath the water lilies' shade.  midst the glade,  the monarch stood,  the regal sovereign of the woods; surrounded by his consorts fair,  the antlered stag here made his lair.  to does,  he flamboyantly flaunts,  to foes,  with carmine pride he taunts; now rests he above the summer bloom,  and draws nearer his impending doom.  a sharp whistle,  it splits the air,  thinner than strands of maiden hair; the spear tip shines with fatal light,  as does and fawns quick took their flight; the forest beasts,  their warnings heed,  all broke into wild stampede; except the stag,  ere he could fly,  dropped lifeless to the ground,  and dies.   in choked grief,  the forest cries,  for this cold-blooded regicide; from afar eyed her blood stained steel,  the assassin within the ferns concealed.  as silence settled across the hills,  the panicked sounds,  they echoed still; till patience expired in her bosom bright,  thus she rose to check her prize.  a fierce maiden,  the mountain's child,  the charming mistress of the wild; cruel scars her ivory skin did borne,  her locks tangled with leaf and thorn.  with starry light and sapphire hue,  never a gaze with zeal so true; nor discover in them a thread of fear,  nor has she shed a single tear.  the sun slants west,  its bright rays dim,  upon her fair and nimble limbs; the burning twilight crimson shone,  on flaxen braids o'er her collarbone.  a fervent heart burns 'neath her crest,  her leather covered snow-white breasts; restrained so they pose no threat,  to her lethal throw nor graceful tread.  with youthful pride the maiden eyed,  her antlered game of the night; the grandest of all forest beasts,  the entree of her evening feast.  now the trophy to her shoulder tied,  and wore as cape the bloody hide; ere the evening chill and night dew falls,  she retreated to her mountain halls.

title: A Goodbye to My First Love
author: a.
text: iâ’m sorry my first and former love for having left so many things unsaid,  for not giving you a hug goodbye,  but alas it is to this that we ourselves have led.  for not wishing a safe journey upon you,  when losing you i could not bear,  perhaps one day youâ’ll understand how i felt,  and just how much i once did care.  you left behind a broken heart but many a happy memory too,  but i never wanted memories,  i only wanted you.  a thousand words couldnâ’t stop this nightmare i know because i tried,  a thousand tears couldnâ’t make me feel better i know because i cried.  but finally i too can say,  itâ’s time,  to go our separate ways,  and that itâ’s time for me to keep trudging alone so that i can find the love of my life someday.  for you are you and i am i,  no longer â“usâ” are we,  alas i guess it was never written in the stars,  just never meant to be.   iâ’ve already lost the naomi i loved and i hope i do not have to lose another,  my best friend,  the person who i once trusted most,  more than any other.  broken promises abound between us,  yes to that i will admit,  for they are a fact of life,  but my promise of friendship i shall try to keep,  i shall not stab your back with a knife.  i miss you a little i guess you could say especially now since youâ’ve gone away,  a little too much although i hate to admit it,  a little too often,  a little bit more each day.   â“but for those truly linked,  companionship and correspondence are trivial.  part of each shall always reside in the heart of the other,  and even after what may seem like a lifetime apart,  their friendship will be truer,  fonder,  and stronger than ever. â” to this i hope but alas if all this was meant to be but a distant memory that we treasure,  then all i ask of you is that you remember me as you go,   on through life until our paths cross again,  if that is meant to be so.   for weâ’ll meet one day in the headlines galore,  if opportunity fails to knock build yourself a door.   life lessons,  great rugby,  stories unreal;  but it was a special girl who made all the same memories surreal.   a thanks to you,  my friend,  for your advice,  love,  passion,  and support to the end.   a dream lies ahead for each memory we treasure,  enough now,  only perfection a new beginning,  itâ’s been a pleasure.

text: it sits there,  looking at you with little less than a glare. .  as you turn the power on,  you realise that the day is gone. .  your eyes blink a single time,  and the sun starts to shine. .  the restroom calls to you,  but you figure a few more hours will do. .  an entire day passed,  not a chore is done,  not a question is asked. .  one more hour you say,   and you don't realise that it's the third day. .  could one be so clueless,  i guess so because it has been a week,  with some hours to spare,  it sits there,  still stareing at you with a little less than a glare.

title: She
author: aditri
text: at the age of five,  she learned that the world was only an oyster for men.  its pearls of wisdom were his alone,  to reap and manipulate as he wished.   her brothers left for school,  full of puerile complaints and she,  enviously from a corner stared.  bitterness was born in her then,  and would stay,  yet no complaint issued from her subdued lips.   resigned not to fate,  but to the will of males,  she lived life as they dictated.  she cooked,  cleaned and bathed the children all the while treated like a cur,  a curse.   everyday her presence was customarily dismissed.  she made tea.  she washed the clothes.  thankless,  leering faces turned to her momentarily then shifted their eyes to more momentous things.   at night,  in the solitude of her dreams,  she envisaged a life that was hers alone.  with morning light the visions dissipated,  as ephemeral as mayflies.   she looked at her daughter,  a joyous bundle at three.  in time,  she would have to learn too.  that the world was only an oyster for men no woman could pry apart those rigid lips.   she wished she could teach her otherwise,  but it was the only way she knew life.

title: Timeless
author: aditri
text: keeper of time,  they called him.  turner of the clock,  weariless winder a young man in his prime,  yet unwithered by winters unencountered.   by day he stood,  silent as a shadow turning the clock till dawn turned to noon,  noon to dusk,  slivers of light painting his visage gold,  red,  silver.   tireless he was,  aye: but he was a man,  and like countless others not fully immune to the endearing charm of the lady of the wood.   a careless whisper,  a sidelong glance,  a gentle caress  was all it took,  and one condition: â“pursue me and you shall have me,  tread where none other does and master the world. â”  lust and avarice,  the twin savants of madness grasped him,  and under their influence he rose.  deserting the clock,  he pursued that tinkling,  silvery laugh,  the material of dreams.   through valley,  rock and scorching plain oceans and deserts alike.  a slave to hope,  deaf to sense he followed the lady of the wood,  and walked to a place beyond the reach of time.   a wondrous place,  of songs unsung a cave aglow with luminous voices.  and there he grasped his maiden for moments innumerable.  before he found he was clutching at air.   yet clutch he did,  clutched at promises unfulfilled,  rapidly dissipating for time had thwarted him,  inducing him to enter the cave beyond time.   then the keeper emerged,  for he knew.  he raced back to the clock,  movements dreamlike.  the clock laughed.  â“foolish keeper,  didnâ’t you know? you stopped keeping time,  now time keeps you. â”

title: Cassie and Wizzy

title: Lebanese Girls in Arab World
author: ala'a
text: once upon a time,  a baby girl was born mother was reveled,  father was a bit scorned.  four years later,  another girl was born,  mother was reveled,  father was a bit scorned.   nine years later,  mother tries to mingle with women of lebanese dresses up her daughters,  tries to make them beauty queens.  women-only parties,  because they were modest with their beauty,  but when it comes to their manners,  it revels in cruelty.   other women with daughters,  who want to marry them to men,  fears that mother's daughters might take away from them.  mother's teen daughter; green eyed,  chubby,  and blonde,  all the other women with daughters wanted her gone.   vicious snakes disguised as women,  tongues flicked,  let loose mother to her daughters: parties no more,  and let's break contact too spring to america: farewell! and said mother too went to lebanon,  with her two daughters,  too.   aunts loved them,  their love sordid,  but the lives they lived were horrid.  white streaks in their hair,  bodies still pure feelings of loneliness and sadness would often occur.   married uncle,  who worships money and lacks humanity,  tries to suck the two aunts' inheritance,  sanity,  and money.  mother says: people who wish good,  nearly none,  mother's daughters laughs and takes it as a pun.   they make a little dance to cheer them up,  and the two aunts' eyes lighted up.

title: WHITE SWAN

text: white swan  as i wait for my friends,  back and forth i survey the land.  a place opposite of mine crafted by his hand i struggle every time we played with the ducks i snort at the sound of their laughter as i stumble w/ the rocks.   i stretch my chalky wings and deep my silver like feathery head my eyes sparkle as i splatter the water up high,  they spread a splendid scene,  hung suspended,  made by the sun meets the dew,  form a crystal drop.  i flew higher than highest and celebrate the view on top.   gravity pulls,  i canâ’t escape the mud.  iâ’m about to slump in to the pond.  i buoyed upward trace my way home,  south wind charge on my direction headlong i rushed through the wave of air w/ a slight convection  time standstill,  i hear a metallic sound of the gun aimed by a gunner.  iron smell- sound the silence,  scent of my flesh aroma of my blood run like a fast runner sunk hapless i am,  betrayed by a shot i hide my best in the nearest bank,  left of corner â–a blackest lot.   melting hopes i think iâ’m dying,  i will miss everything voices echo my throbbing head,  family,  inhuman beauty,  and living i am a swan - lovely as what love can be,  i need to be strong and go on iâ’m aching but iâ’ll heal iâ’ll never forget what this pain taught â“hold onâ”  i step outside and gaze at my reflection,  new aura cover my innocence.  raven,  ready for revenge yet i calm and remember a swan essence.

title: The Pain
author: allison
text: the pain is the worst pain in the world it is not merely the pain of a broken arm,   that heals with time nor is it the pain of a starving child,   that can be fed this pain attacks your soul,   and claws at it with furious fingers there is only one thing strong enough to bring such pain love.  it is two-faced yes love is wonderful,  glorious,  but only when it is returned if love has left you abandoned,  then you know the pain of which i speak it twists you,  ringing out every thought and emotion you dont want to think or feel it punches you,  knocking out the happiness that was left it squashes you,  until you are no more than a hollow shell it is then that the pain fills you,  howling into your disembodied body like a triumphant vortex and you think you can still go on,  as long as you are filled with something,  you can seem to be basically human but you're not.  death merely stands before you,  and you throw yourself at him,  begging with the last thread of sanity you have left to take you with him anywhere.  for some,  he obeys their wishes he ends their pain,  and releases their beaten and battered souls  into the blissful unknown.  but he does not end your suffering,  simply cassting your clinging hands off his white cloak.  that is the last time you cry,  the last time you feel emotion at all after all,  if death doesn't want you,  who will?

title: A REALM OF AN INSIDE MIND
author: amanda
text: i cant explain what goes on in my mind nor the pain i feel.  i can remember when i used to smile and i can remember the laughter i hear aloud.  over the years of growing up i have noticed the pain,  the smiles and laughter had slowly begun to fade.  i had an image of what my life should have been but in the realm of my inside mind what i saw for for my life was nothing but imperfections and tightened disasters.  pain seeps my heart sorrows drain my soul.  my deepest feelings sentimental but drawness of perfections old.  i lived my life the best i knew to do.  have searched my heart though and through. never felt like i was ever wanted always threw off the side as if i was a nobody.  words spoken of i hate you empty hearted and still thought eco the realm of my inside mind.

title: Losing You
author: amanda
text: i cry at night thinking of you.   i thought you said you loved me too?  why did you lie to me so much?   you know i used to melt at your touch.   now your gone,  out of my life.   you left without saying goodbye.    i'm not the only person you hurt.   you hurt your family & your friends.   why did you let the drugs do the talking?  why didn't you resist the rope?   the tears i cry are tears of pain.   you've made not only my life a living hell.   your dad took it bad as well.   you know he loved you so why did you go?  you never knew my feelings i know.    i wish now that i would have told you.   although you said you never liked me like that.    i liked it when we talked on the phone,  i  would've done it more if i was a person who liked  talking on the phone.   i like chatting in person better,  but what we had  was a nice little chat.    you were the sweetest,  funniest andd the most  easy-going and friendly of almost all of your friends.   not to mention,  you were great at sports,  had a job  at an electric company,  and was only 20 when you  let yourself be missed forever.    you had a girl,  that's what you had told me two  weeks b4 over the phone.   you told me you never liked me ''like that'' and the  one simple rumor i'm supposed to hate you for  was all your friends' fault.    they were the ones who had said we slept together.   i know you wanted me to believe you,  but my neighbor,   whom i've known forever wouldn't lie to hurt me like that.   i know him too well,  of course now i wish it had been true.    i was always hoping and dreaming that we would be together  forever,  that we would have children together and live happily  ever after like in a fairy tale.    i want a tattoo in your memory,  but my dad said that i will regret it later,  but i know i never will.  he said he would have thought about it if i wanted a butterfly or something,  but i'll just have to wait a few months until i'm 18.    i love you too much not to remember you and even if i do find someone else,  i'll remember you as the best friend i ever had!

title: We Are Free
author: angela
text: i sometimes wake up in the morning and wonder,  ''why does god waste his time on me?'' as wake up i thank god for another beautiful day he has allowed me to wake up to.  as i go through my day i notice things,  just small things that god has provided that too many times are taken for granted.  the birds chirping,  the sun shining,  the green grass.  but most of all i notice how free we as americans are.  we dont think about it often. . . but did you ever notice that there is nobody ever holding a gun to our heads telling us if we pray out loud,  we will die? did you ever notice that we are free to go to church and worship how we please? one of the biggest things i think we as christians take for granted,  is god.  did you ever notice that no matter how far away you are from god,  when you turn around there he is with open arms wanting nothing more but to claim you as one of his own?

title: My burden
author: anike
text: no one knows how much it grows when i hear ''you're not good enough''  my black sphere sits on my back between my knees underfoot,  overhead kindling a feeling of dread a net of electrified wire around my heart.   yet,  when you ask how i am ''hey,  i'm doing good,  how about you fam?'' appearances are never what they seem a faked gleam in my eye,  a mimicked confidence a white lie oh please,   believe me when i say ''no thanks,  i'm okay''  help,  i'd like to say help my black ball go away i'm choking and drowning on its wispy darkness.  the light filtering down above my head is getting fainter as i sink deeper and deeper into my black hole.   voices,  too many voices do you know how hard it is to be functionally depressive? sinister whispers of unachieved potential belie every  moment of happiness i could ever dream of enjoying.   yes,  i have friends.  the trouble is,  they don't look too closely.  my burden hides well in my corners and crevices and wrinkles and dimples it shapeshifts from weighty ball to second skin a translucent gray mist my shroud,  my shield.

title: The Sun and the Moon
author: anna
text: the sun sets down off into the horizon,   the yellow hue reminded us of the warmth it provided.   the many different colors of the sunset blended and collided.   as they get thinner and less diverse and slowly blend,   we all gather and watch as the sunset reaches its end.   as the rainbow of color all go to dark,  lovely blue,   we see godâ’s goodness fully shine through.   all this we see and know through the horizon.    the moon now rises up and brings a new light,   we watch it come up and fit through the stars.   the white and gray figure is now like a croissant.   the small glow surrounding it gives us a little sight.   the people around me are heading to their cars  all saying that this was such a wonderful night!

title: Sleepless Nights
author: anna
text: ding dong,  ding!  itâ’s twelve oâ’clock  i know what that means  itâ’s time for the monsters to come out and play.   first they hide under my bed  then they move to the shadows  and finally they end up inside my head.   of course no one has seen them,   except for me  because i am the only one  who can truly see.   first i see spiders  then i see clowns  and finally i see my own demons come out.   i like to just lay  and watch them play  until i get sleepy  and i ask them to please go away.   sometimes i wonder,  after i fall asleep  have they really gone away  or are they just waiting for me  to overcome my own evils.   the only way i would find out  was if i truly could,   but until then  iâ’ll be sure to see my monsters  and tell them thanks  for all my sleepless nights.

title: Hers
author: annie
text: with a handful of sand  she began her castle;  one she knew would fall,   but for now it was beautiful.    she placed each glob of ocean soaked sand precisely,   not just for looks,  but for structure.   nothing can last forever,   but a while is still nice.    she took a step back to get a better view,   and placed a few shells here and there.   it was unique.   there would never be another.    and as a wave came up and removed the base,   it crumbled under the weight.  yet she still smiled for it,   no matter what happened,  she loved her castle,   because it was perfect,   and it was perfect because it was hers.

title: Left

text: mercy languidly withdraws her wing  sighing easily as though  she had given up a burden,  and  her wing does not casually brush or cause to fall over  the weary multitudes whom under her comforting rustle had rested  mere moment chance to pause for rest.  suddenly gone,   exposing us to the  raging torrent,  sheâ’s lifting herself higher soaring now ,  while we are heavily grounded.  bare,  plain in sight to predators both around  and above,  here they come swooping down to devour us.  and as my suffering  approaches in final fade,  i spot quick secret glance,   the lift of an eyelid,   the slight drop in her flight while distracted,  shocked at the fate sheâ’s left us to but will not offer aid,  refuses to come save us.  where is mercy? she has despised us.

title: Remembering Sunshine
author: aroko
text: remembering sunshine   scared awake  almost at sunrise with a sensed disturbance  of balance,  icicles waiting to drip from budding trees as i sun tan in january with my wish for spring fulfilled.  the signs say this is the day where a new story begins,  if iâ’m not careful my expectations will shatter this still water with a clumsy touch.  should i stop searching  or is being alive always a search anyway? i can finally sit in comfort without my eager instincts pushing me out the door like our black cat in heat calling to the other side,  possessed by the power of creation.  so with this in mind i settle on a warm winter bench,  aware in my happiness  that i am not the man screaming â“shut upâ” to my companion who spasms in a new direction with the disgust of feeling lifeless even on the day where we finally remember sunshine.

title: Chill
author: arthur
text: last night i dreamed of chickens,  there were chickens everywhere,  they were standing on my stomach,  they were nesting in my hair,  they were pecking at my pillow,  they were hopping on my head,  they were ruffling up their feathers as they raced about my bed.   they were on the chairs and tables,  they were on the chandeliers,  they were roosting in the corners,  they were clucking in my ears,  there were chickens,  chickens,  chickens for as far as i could see. . .  when i woke today,  i noticed there were eggs on top of me.

title: Venus Cracks
author: arthur
text: volcanos on venus  the liquid fire of io shoots magma 250 miles into the blackness of space.   triton spits frozen nitrogen and moon dust far into the universe and when the sun warms the surface it bursts through like a geyser and sprays the face of jupiter with a fiery mist.   europa is stretched by the gravity of jove where behind a layer of ice lives a breathing ocean.  all this unseen motion  runs the circuitry of the cosmos 170 moons in our solar system a billion solar systems in a galaxy a billion more in the vast cosmic web  my love  an incomprehensibly small flicker in the enigmatic night resounds more in all this in a trillion,  trillion years  beloved.

title: Pinecones
author: ashley
text: pinecones  pinecones hold memories  of late afternoon football matches and making birdfeeders with mother.   of bonfires and sâ’mores and camping and raking leaves with father.   of long ride homes from university and thanksgiving dinners with family.   in their fragile petals,  they hold them,  secret and silent,  watching all the time.   melancholy recollections,  of growth and change and the passing of seasons.   pinecones hold memories,  as well as potential.   they rest humbly,  watching,  forgetting that they,  too,  can transform

title: Walking the Moonlight
author: asna
text: i walk the hill by the moonlight,  quiet and solitary with no one beside.  i hear the night creatures speak a language of their own,  asking each other perhaps,  if the intruder is known.   i walk the hill by the moonligt quiet and solitary,  with no one beside.  i see the yawning flowers sway calmly with the wind,  trying to glance perhaps,  at me,  not of thier kin.   i walk the hill not anymore since then,  quiet and solitary,  devoid of a friend.  i stay in my yard and reflect on the pretty sights,  the sights i remember when walking the moonlight.

title: To You
author: atanas
text:
a sharp arrow hit me in the back and its metal point reached my heart. now i lie down bleeding from within and i donâ’t even know if i can make it before i begin. no matter how hard i try to take the arrow out all i can do is shout. i shout with words that no one but god can hear and all day long i cry without shedding a single tear. sometimes somehow i manage to get away and even forget the pain i struggle with every day but thatâ’s just until the next morning comes when i see the one who makes my aching heart pounds then my body starts shivering in pain again and all i want to do is speed up in the fast lane. numerous times i have tried to pull the arrow out but could never really reach out. o, how much i want to ease the pain and make it disappear like a winter rain. i pray about it every day hoping that the pain will go away. yes, i know that to any torment there is an end but now is the moment i need to vent. <
if one thing would remain with you after reading this please let it be this: if there is a woman you love, who loves you, never let her go! many guys out there long for such a person but have never had one!

title: That Girl
