text: this girl was crazy.  she had an annoying name.  i hated it when she saw me,  because she was just that insane.  her mind was made of evil,  and nothing about her was right.  when only her fake smile, was the main thing she tried to hide.  i finally told her about you,  and how your actions give you a great look.  after telling her about us two,  that was pretty much all it took.  she has nothing else to hide,  and she is proud of her name.  what i told her of you was alright,  and now she will never be the same.  the girl was like that all the time,  but she is still a little crazy.  when i told her that you were on my mind.  i realized the girl in the mirror,  was me.  i appreciate what i do.  i no longer kick myself on the floor.  all i needed was a blessing of meeting you.  i don't know that girl anymore.

 there,  where ever you are the sun is always shining,  the birds are always singing,  and people are always healing,  each other and offering help â– support and seeking happiness throughout their working  in my world,  there is no problems need solving no people combatting,  no hard living there is nothing without meaning!! title: The man on the Porche
author: bekki
text: there once was a young man with a black suit that used to sit on the porche of a elegant canadian home.   he didn't mean anyone harm,  just wanted to sit on the porche in a chair.   he puffed on his cigarette in his 1912 suit.   the owners of the house,  a young mother and daughter,  told him repeatedly to get lost.   sometimes he would leave,  sometimes he wouldn't.   then they had to call the police to take him away.   he stsayed away for a while,  a month went by and turned into summer.   then,  the daughter spotted him outside again.   so she rushed out the door and stormed right up to him.   vixy:what is your problem huh,  how come you won't leave?  he smoked so elegantly on his cigarette before turning to her.   the warm wind blowing his blonde hair back.   his icy blue eyes stared into hers.   then,  in a voice as smooth as snow,  he said:  thomas:well my dear,  i died here.   she gasped in horror at the fact,  that she was staring at a ghost.   she didn't know that.   she backed away and ran.   she told her mom later that afternoon what had happened.   she gasped and ran outside.   but he wasn't there,  he had disappeared.   apparently,  he chose heaven instead.   yeah,  they're much nicer up there.   so things went fine,  but they never forgot the place where the ghost died.

title: A letter to a Friend
author: beulah
text: dearest fren…. ,                when we first met….           you had strange n mysterious eyes,           ones that always drew me to you,           made me wonder what you were going through,           never expected fate would bring us so close…………. .           you always had your way with me,          cause you had become one of my weakness,          one that made me strong…         knowing your story i was always afraid,          afraid of the choices youl make,          afraid of the chances youl take,          afraid of the mistakes youl make,         but never did i let my fear reflect,         never did i impose anything,  spoke only when i had to,         always letting you choose and live your life your way,          i made you equal with my closest frens        but you  never realized it.        i forgave you whenever you were dishonest,       realizing  i wasnâ’t perfect either      but as time went on…………………     you could not do the same,      you made conclusions and left saying you were still there. . ,      it hurt so much as lonliness hugged me. . ,      i tried to move on,  trying to let go of everything…     it was hard but pain had changed me,      not for worse but better…. ,      i had been scared of losing you but not anymore,      surprised that all the fears i had for you had receded,     all this does not mean that my love for you has changed. . ,     its just that i want to let you have your way as always,    and that im willing to wait no matter how long it takes   and no matter what it costs me,  even if i go unnoticed,    just as i promised to be faithful and true till my last breath…   not just because i value my words but because i value you……. .                                                                                                    love you always,                                                                                                       your friend…. .

title: Dear Friend
author: beyoncã©
text: dear friend,  it has been long since we last talked,  but your presence is present through the inanimate things youâ’ve given me: memories,  cards,  notifications.   dear friend,  i remember how we would tell jokes and how our laughter rang  like a broken phone  throughout the halls of the cozy house.   dear friend,  we are 9, 893 miles apart but our friendship is strong enough  to build a bridge made of loyalty,  trust,  respect,  and humor over stormy waters.   dear friend,  donâ’t worry.  you cross my mind more than you know as i think about how much more we have to grow,  about our plans for the future and how weâ’re going to travel and enjoy life as it comes.   dear friend,  i canâ’t wait to see you soon.  our jigsaw puzzle personalities,  and jokes we save for each other that we locked in the cage that is our hearts and the purple bags of popcorn that we devour as we turn into animals while watching cutthroat kitchen.    dear friend,  i hope that your life right now is as perfect as your charisma,  because you deserve only the best.  and i hope that you take care of yourself,  and that wherever life takes you,   you make the best of it.

title: Take me away
author: bhavani
text: for little girls who want to run away from everything ever possible it is hard.  i have tried.  and survived.  every.  setback.  every.  attack.  this is not an easy task; nor is it a tough one.  many perceive the life of a runaway  to be a frightened existence drenched in raindrops cold and steel blue flitting through dark alleyways filled with tabbycats and scrawny puppies  we are all looking for shelter.  scratch that.  we were all looking for shelter.  and perhaps the darkness is sometimes the greater comfort ensconced in trash can liners eye liner dripping the onlooker looks on,  believing they look through the individual with pity and sorrow and such yet,  the black lines tracing the apples of her cheeks must not simply be inferred as a sign of maltreatment.   this is for the little girls.  those who want to runaway from everything ever possible.  donâ’t be afraid of what is out there.  it may even be a big,  bad world but it is only through the darkest nights that the moon shines bright light.  the hold of your hands,  the poise in the way you stand are gifts enough to give this world-that hungers for beauty.  pain too and forgiveness.  we need so much more to feel today.  the graceful hand movements replaced.   if you look yourself in the eye,  and your eyes are glass beads,   if you frown,  and see beauty,  if you fall in love with yourself even in moments of boredom.  you can say it with me.  we might all be little girls yearning to run through wheat filled blue skied fields with the red polka dot dresses and straw hats with ribbons in our hair.   this is for you.   the little girl who wants to runaway from everything ever possible. . . you are more than you ever thought you could be and you become more,  every                                                          single                                                                 day.

title: The best love story
author: bha
text: he is a knight in a shining armor she is a charming princess they both looked into each other's eyes he saw the vast ocean she saw her world.  they wished to hug so tight  that all their worries may vanish.  to join all the broken pieces of heart.  she made him feel special he kept looking at her from distance.  he wished to help her but  something stopped him it was the concern he had for her.  he didn't want her to get hurt.  she understood and smiled.  she contains herself from the fear of losing him.   she withdraws herself in the shell.  she wish to heal his wounds,  to be with him,  to love him when he is down,  to fight for him they make an effort to start afresh.  she rises his spirits high he makes her crazy and wild she longs for a soul he wanted a beautiful heart.  both knew they were perfect for each other.  its then circumstances and situations crept in.  they had to part their ways.  she believed in destiny and in the love she had for him.   when he smiles,  she smiles she craves for his happiness her dreamy eyes are mirror to her soul his voice soothes her troubled spirit she wants to take him to the cloud nine which she dreams of he loses himself in her.    she showed her vulnerability it made him ran away she puts up her fight which still continues.  he taught her self respect she taught him to be expressive there was much to those loving glances they didn't want to become strangers again.  she wants to try her best before she walks away.   god planned the most amazing love story  their love is tested.  she can walk through fire to claim him she built the castle for her king he adores his queen she trusted her intuition and is waiting.   i am what i am and you are what you are that's what makes us unique and perfect !!  the passion burnt brighter in her heart finally her dreams can true he walked towards her and the distance between them abridged they made a promise with their eyes  to never leave each other .  the angels blessed this beautiful union a match made in heaven completed.

title: A Girl Within
author: blanche
text: a little girl within    a little girl with a past so bleak,    painful memories make her weak.    a little girl with no one to care,    found out early that life's unfair.    a little girl with nowhere to turn   maybe one day she will learn.     a little girl with a past so bleak,    painful memories still make her weak.    years pass by,  but the pain seems to stay,    wondering when it will all go away.    a young woman with no where to turn,    hoping for the day she will learn.     a little girl with a past so bleak,    painful memories making her weak.    never knowing what to do,    dealing with the pain she's been through.    a loving woman with no where to turn,    wishing for the day the little girl will learn.     a little girl deep down inside,    is what this woman tries to hide,    she tries harder day by day   to keep the hurt hidden away.    but the little girl will never learn,    leaving this woman with no where to turn.     a little girl deep within,    never allowing the pain to end.

title: Bowels of Honey
author: brandon
text: i open my head like the cork of a bottle  the secret place where i keep the honey yellow liquid,  smooth in texture,  sweet in taste.    i reach inside to scoop some out then i place it in a bowl.   the honey helps me make lots of friends the bowl a catalyst to make amends if an acquaintance feels a certain way then happiness the honey may.   i reach in to gather more honey gathering deeper and deeper,  exploring the dark hidden chasms in my mind.  must i push myself so harshly?  endanger myself for a quick release? however,  with more honey comes more friends and without friends,  how will i live? such risks may be worth taking  i wipe the spare honey off the side of the bowl then take a quick taste to appease my soul i look at my shelf,  which there is not enough i need more honey of which i hope they will love.   soon i empty myself of honey,  causing the chasms to hollow out without my happy thoughts to soothe,  they begin to quake in anger and pain.  i grab a knife,  curiosity driving me forwards until i run out,  then emptiness halting me.    i place it down,  now all i have is my honey  soon my friends arrive,  and i offer them all my honey deep down i only wish it helps them on their journey they take their fill,  then leave without warning they leave me alone,  with empty bowls and mourning.   i love offering honey to my friends and family i just wish i could get something back iâ’m starving my mind is now hollow,  cavernous and a scary place without happiness to ease it.  yet i continue on,  ignorant to what my ideas may say to me.    everybody claims the best part about me is my honey.  if only i could have some for me.

text: looking out upon a rock,  seeing earthâ’s beauty so well,  i couldnâ’t talk if i could stay here everyday it would be hard for me to go away sunshine's bright,  the trees are green mountainous size boulders reigning over me  the rocks are warm from the sun's kiss,  wild and rigid with standing natureâ’s test.  a lone tree blows gently between a small crack,  his other friends are further away as if he had lost track around here standards are low,  this rock is a home even if we donâ’t think so.   skies are vivid,  glowing blue,  cascading over this rocky view.  what can nature say more to this? except that this is primal bliss.  no expectations,  no intruding quarrel to this bundle of rocks,  its only soil.   our eyes are magical in a sense we may forget capturing beauty from a thing made of sand and grit we see what we believe and nothing more because our attitude seeks whatâ’s in our core though some may think itâ’s just a pile of rocks but to you and i itâ’s earthâ’s building blocks.

title: Escape
author: brianna
text: september 4th,  2015.  bbc news.   â“hundreds of migrants stuck at a budapest railway station… intend to walk to austria. â”  hundreds of people walking hundreds of miles.   every face is desperate forâ—what?  peace? security? order?  what is it they seek?  something they can no longer find in their cities.   in their towns.   in their own backyards.   every day is a test for the mothers who can longer say,  â“it will be alright. â”  when your way of life is so threatened that you cannot tell your enemy from your neighbor,   what is there to do but flee?  leave,  and you risk your life.  stay,  and you risk your death.   eventually you will have been afraid for so long that you will hardly even notice.   nights will feel longer.   days will feel so dangerous that the terror will threaten  to strangle every ounce of hope  you have left.   the house that has been home for so long  is threatening to collapse in on itself  and the people are dying to escape.   these people are not walking.   they are running.

title: Black Blood
author: brianna
text: he dwells in darkness beyond where no one can reach.  he lies in his own pool of black blood that lays about.   finally,  he had come to realize his poison has seeped into his bloodbath.  and although he knew how tainted he had become,  he had yet to see what it had done to his surroundings throughout.    his surroundings are black and tainted in his blood,  just as it always had,  but where has everyone gone,  so beyond his reach? they all have fled from this place for the blood poisons them and they vomit out of rejection,  escaping into the distance as he watches them fadeout.   but he has,  however,  attracted some travelers who have crossed his path.   they,  too,  have the black blood as it was proven beyond any doubt.    it is because they are leeches that will suck him dry,  just as he would them,  until they are nothing and leave them to die in their own black blood as a spineless pathetic leech.  but,  heâ’s lain in this blood far too long to count.  and he must crawl out its blackness and rid himself of this poison,  for he has no choice but to do so in the aftermath.   because of the ad-cursive righteous light,  the light that has finally exposed his wrongdoings,  he now,  must face the blood within himself that has seeped out.

title: Goodbye
author: brianna
text: memories frolic in the heart of my mind.  those times of when we loved,  shared smiles,  and treasured every moment together.  those times of hatred and angry that were washed away with the sands of time in the tides of our fondness altogether.  all have become an everlasting footprint for my heart to journey with until the end of mankind.    but,  now our lives have become a crossroad and it appears our wonderful voyage has reached its end,  our bond of rare-kind.  my heart stops,  my eyes water,  and my body trembles to the thought of our departure,  but it is not me who wishes to dismember our bond,  our delicate feather.  it is life who sows our separate lives and will assort us in our proper destinations for us to endeavor.  but,  life is a mysterious creature whose unseen works may twine our lives together and rekindle the light of our friendship,  our bond of rare-kind.    and,  if  life does,  indeed,  tie our lives together,  then,  surely,  our friendship will be forevermore,   dwelling in the realms of eternal life of our divine.  so,  if we truly must depart,  let it be with a joyous smile and a warm heart,  for although we depart,  our friendship will flourish with every passing day and never sever.  and so it is with this,  i bid you a goodbye,  but not a goodbye to our lives,  our bond,  or our love,  its beauty as elegant as a white feather.  no,  it is only goodbye for now and hope for a prosperous future,  for as life shall have it,  we were destined to be together forever entwine.

title: The Madness of Fear
author: brianna
text: a smirk creeps from the rim of my lips in gladness.  finally,  it has seep into my spirit and now governs my soul,  my dearest madness.  for,  deep within the recesses of my consciousness lurks a gruesome creature who feeds upon many entities,  but the entity of fear the foremost.  it feasted upon my fear and its belly swelled as it began to evolved,  too large for the human mind to engross.     so,  it abandoned its home and hollowed itself a new home within the depths of my soul of sadness.  and there,  it dictates my behavior and monitors every aspect of mental notion i make,  my dearest madness.   it tells me to fear the outside,  for diseases will slither into my body and will cause me terrible illness,  so i do not go beyond my fencepost.  it tells me to be afraid of others,  for they are the ones who hoard these diseases that will cause me terrible illness,  and so i avoid others from every coast.    this beast continues to execute its commands,  and after years of dictatorship,  it forged itself into madness.  and finally,  i have succumbed to its control and cease my struggle to resist in sadness.  upon comprehending this,  the beast whispers inside me: â“you are such a weak and frail host.  a child whose  doubts of life conceived a fear,  and,  thorough time,  it grew beyond your control and conceived meâ”,  he boasts.  but now,  you stand powerless,  unable to relinquish your fear because of  what i've become and it is now your fear that i have become that you fear the very most.

author: brittney
text: i see a boy with distant eyes,  he smiles,  but you can see the pain.   he wears a mask upon his little face,  and i have yet to know his name.   i heard his parents call him many things a child should not hear.  and with those nicknames thrown about,   the child shows no fear.   such a colorful selection,  i might add,  on his parents' behalf.  who gave their child nothing more to travel on,  but a lonely and beaten path.   will this boy ever find the place that's right for him? only time will tell and someone's help can make him safe again.

title: My Votech Class
author: brittney
text: my votech class means everything to me,  its my favorite time of the day.  every afternoon,  i anticipate seeing my construction friends,  knowing that we get to work together,  as a team,  until the school year ends.  but this class offers more than just a specific group of skills.  its more than just a place to go if you wanna learn to build.  its a place where i can be myself,  around others with the same interests as me.  where a girl can fit in with the rest of the guys,  and one's not judged on by their abilities.  and yes,  i've had my share of bad days too,  just like everyone else.  and there have been times when i shed a few tears,  but its okay,  cuz there's always been someone there to help.  if i have a problem,  with school or at home,  the teacher is always there if i need to talk.  he tries to help me out,  in any way he can,  so that the problem doesn't bother me around the clock.  some days are easy,  while others are not.  it all depends on my mood,  but if there's one thing i've learned,  at the end of each day,  it really pays off to have a good attitude.  in a class where you literally give your blood,  sweat,  and tears,  and have a passion for the things that you make. . . there is a joy that comes from just being yourself and knowing that you've got what it takes.  and with the friendships i've made with my peers and the staff,  it will be hard to say goodbye.  but at the end of the year,  when its my time to leave,  i can't guarantee,  that i won't break down and cry.  because this class has given me much more than any class has.  its opened my eyes and set me on a new path.  but i know,  once i'm gone,  there's no turning back,  i can only move ahead.  but there may come a time,  when i can come back,  to maybe just visit instead.

title: Fly Away
author: brittney
text: fly away birdy,  fly away.  you've grown your wings,  now go and play.  do explore your world around. . .  from sea to sea,   and town to town.  don't let the wind blow you away.  hold tight to your course,  don't fall astray.   but i want you to know,  if something goes wrong,   just fly back to this nest. . .  and into these arms.

title: If I Were A Potato...

title: Six Letters
author: brooklynn
text: \t â“six lettersâ”   it takes six letters to wrap its hand around anyone and take their life.  they say that words have a lot of power,  but i would give up having control of writing if that one word lost its power.   life isnâ’t about controlling.    it isnâ’t about gaining ownership over someone who breaks away from dreams just to live in a bitter reality.   writing isnâ’t painful,  so why should those six letters be?  life was about racing friends down crooked sidewalks,   riding bicycles until the scrapes on our knees were unbearable,  freezing with the slight touch of a hand on our shoulders,  praying a prayer of prideful palification,  wishing a wish that wouldnâ’t end in wounding wayment.   i was taught that love is not crippling,   and that it wouldnâ’t rip the tendoning feelings from my heart.   iâ’ve seen these six letters beat people blue and make their hair fall from their head like a waterfall.   i watched the crippling chemo shatter people into broken puzzle pieces.  i have loved people who have endured,   dwelled,   suffocated,   in these six letters.   words. .  words hold so much more than just letters.   iâ’m a writer,  but that word erases me.   iâ’m a lover,  but that word hates me.   i can walk,  but that word cripples me.   love is one word worth knowing.   but what can you do,  when your love intertwines fingers with six letters?  what can you do when you canâ’t tell your loved one that theyâ’ll get better?  six letters has a name.   cancer.   let me tell you this,   if six letters were a person i would personally open up a fresh can of hope on them.   weâ’re taught that words donâ’t define who we are.  but when it comes to people who are unlucky enough to have this,   words do.   so this is for them.   donâ’t ever apologize to others,  because you didnâ’t do anything to catch this.   this is for those who have loved ones who are embracing this.  donâ’t ever believe for one second that itâ’s unbeatable.   hope is the only word that should hold ownership over anything.   let it hold ownership over you.   this is for those who have lost loved ones to this.   i would apologize.  but apologies are just understatements to how people feel.   it takes six letters to wrap itsâ’ hand around anyone and take their life.   they say that words have a lot of power,  so this is for her.   even though cancer brought her to godâ’s gates,  she beat it.   cancer is just six letters.

title: The Passing Of A Great Man
author: c
text: on february,  2nd 1996 a great man passed  away into a peaceful  place.  a place that puts all your heartâ’s,  mindâ’s,   and soulâ’s to the  test.  memories flood through your minds  of the way things were  before.  you picture a time when you awaited his return home,  or a knock at your door.  although our hearts are saddened that those days have gone by,   remember that james                     truly will never die.  in each of his children,  and grand children he lives on in very special ways,   that will keep him alive in our hearts forever.  his strength lives in the confidence of  his sonâ’s walk.  his witty charm lives on in his daughterâ’s  talk forever.  his sense of humor he gave to us all,  and too all he knew.  his pride that has kept us all  walking tall.   his thoughts,  his ideas,  and his jokes he  gave to all he knew.  a man of honor who kept his words  faithful,  and true.  my grandpa was loved,  and respected by many.   he always gave himself to others he had plenty.  even though his body got tired,  and wore out i will not forget and let die what my grandpa was all about.  today we have been departed he will always be alive in our hearts,  and look for the day when we all awaited his return or a knock at my door

title: No Longer
author: cameron
text: i no longer want to live.  no that's not true.  i no longer want to live like this.  i want to not exist in this numbing purgatory i've ended up in after my world has fairly recently crumbled and fallen to the ground surrounding me.  it hurts: this numbness,  something i have never personally known,  but knew existed,  and never believed it would become my reality.    i try so hard to break through back to my own freedom like my other half so easily has,  but that's not what i want.  she did. .  so the harder i push the more constricted and trapped and hurt i become.  this hurts me so deeply.  i ache and cry.  these wounds will never truly heal,  and the scars they leave will disfigure my heart and leave my mind damaged and traumatized forever.  i am ruined.    or am i now in possession of a painful but useful wisdom? i try to be positive and see the usefulness in this situation,  this agony.  but she keeps thrusting the knife back into my heart.  deeper and deeper with every turn.  how can anyone hurt someone so badly and be happy? it's human nature to be selfish and concerned with oneâ’s own happiness but this.  i don't know how to explain what i feel so i continuously write story after story,  poem after poem hoping to come across an answer and i've found many.  but not the right one.  so i continue my search through this hell.  this empty purgatory that at the same time is full of so many crushing emotions that put the weight if the sun on my shoulders.  i'm tired though,  i don't want to continue the search even though i will regardless.    i don't want to love anymore.  no that's not true - i don't want to love like this any longer

title: Daydreaming
author: carl
text: it was a stormy monday morning and i found myself seating in math class,  daydreaming.  but this was no mere daydream this dream felt as thought is were real,  the colors were loud,  bright and full of emotion,  daydreaming.    the sounds of the class bleed out of the reach of my ears until i was no longer seated there in class,  daydreaming.   the storm that was tapping at the window of the class seemed to have subsided and the sun was the main object in the sky,  daydreaming.   no longer was i a number in a school of countless thousands,  i was one person,  one soul,  one heart beat,  daydreaming.   the world that had cast a spell on me crumbled,  and then i was able to breath life into the world that i created,  daydreaming.   this daydream was everything that i wanted my life to be,  a fair world,  unlimited amounts of peace,  year long springs  and most of love,  daydreaming.  but by the ringing of the bell my world faded just as fast as it came.

title: More Than Words
author: celest
text: like a summer breeze,  like a winter fire,  like the air i breath,  like the lord i admire,   do you understand my words,  do you have a clue,  ask me the question,  what does poetry do?  it creates a new place,  it expands a small world,  walking the highest valley,  with your best boy or girl.   lets me get away,  from a troubled life,  always so blue and dark,  for this i forever write,   like the first flower blooming,  like a childs first steps,  like the family moments,  that you never forget,   like the early singing of the early birds.  can't explain it,  it's just more than words.

title: My Room

text: looking around at my room i see blue but no sign of the gloom.  my sheets show me fish,  i see a spare dish,  and maybe it could use a broom.   my shoes are all strewn on the floor and there's a big,  shiny lock on the door.  it protects me from crooks,  the desk has all my books,  and i bet you there's no room for more!  laying here,  my bed is so warm,  all wrapped up,  listening to the storm.  it may be tiny,  but to me it's new and shiny,  and always much better than a dorm!

title: Gods Grace
author: chelsea
text: my life never seems to be very good,  itâ’s dark and gloomy with nothing but fear,  everyone looks so happy like they should,  i try to smile but along comes tears:  while i ponder between the truth and lies,  my thoughts and heart will never be the same,  you can see my pain looking through my eyes,  i know no matter what iâ’m not to blame:   but in time i know life will get better,  i have taken the grace of god  to thought,  i know my eyes will be even wetter,  when god shines down and saves me from the drought:  donâ’t be so quick to think you have nothing,  god may not be clear but he says something.

title: A Slave of Music
author: chelsea
text: the music starts alone at first,  its partner is unknown.  out of the darkness,  a light appears and a girl steps forth.  her head snaps back,  and her body slackens,  as she becomes something else.  the music takes hold of her,  begging her to dance with him.  da-dun! she snaps into series of jumps,  one after another as if sheâ’s possessed.  da-dun! she stops and lifts her head,  pausing for a moment.  her hand reaches up as if to grab something no one else can see,  hoping.  da-dun! sheâ’s ripped from the dream,  and thrown into another bout of spins and stamping,  like a caged-wild animal.  the music has a hold of her,  spinning,  twirling,  kicking,  when bam! she hits the floor and is still.   the music is silently waiting.  a war is going on inside of her,  her body rises and falls.   her arms and legs are heavy with submission,  like there are weights strapped to each wrist and ankle.  wait! her body stirs.  her arms begin to slide underneath her along with her legs,  and slowly,  like a newborn,  she rises.  the music starts to try and step in,  not wanting to let go.  the girlâ’s head snaps up,  eyes wild yet focused,  and the music stops in surprise.  she straightens and steps out of the light,  walking with ease.

title: Where are you shoes?!

title: Tick Tock
author: chloe
text: she lay there,  on the bed,   mouth slightly agape.   her heavy breaths came slowly but left quick.   tick tock,  tick tock.    the room was dull and colourless.   the only light came from a large window,  which seemed to always be in hiding from the sun.   tick tock,  tick tock.    her body so weak yet her heart so strong.   occasionally she would groan or cough or try to speak,  but nothing only mumbles.   tick tock,  tick tock.    tortured by piercing eyes,  staring at her,   watching,  waiting for her to die.   the caressing of her hands,  her legs and her arms.   the odd joke or laugh about things she had done in the past,  slowly replaced by tears.   tick tock,  tick tock.    the vultures arrived,  nodding solemnly and whispering 'hello'.   i hated them.   a tear shed,  but no more than one.    tick tock,  tick tock.    people crowded the room,  once i counted 25.    25 people in one tiny,  cramped room.   the smell of broken hope hung heavy in the air.   tick tock,  tick tock.    the sound of sniffling noses,  the crumpling of tissue packets,   the small quiet tear filled whispers saying 'it's okay to let go'.   until finally,  she did.

title: The Best Friend I've Ever Had
author: chris
text: the air swirled around me in the early hours of a sunday morning.  i sat underneath an old willow tree in the park just a few feet away from the edge of a pond.  the sun was shining with such purity and innocence that my thoughts were put on hold as i admired itâ’s beauty.  beneath the willow tree i sat,  and a few feet away was the best friend iâ’ve ever had,  underneath a similar tree,  enveloped in thought.  he and i had known each other since birth.  through thick and thin,  he was there with me,  always.  though inseparable we seemed,  he sometimes went and many lonely moments i spent longing for him to return.  we are alike in so many ways,  we could be twins.  the same warmth fills our faces when we look into the sky.  the same sadness fills our hearts when one another feels pain.  through and through weâ’ve stuck together,  and many years we will spend,  too.  i knew this was to be true as i sat there in the early hours of a sunday morning,  peering into the water at the reflection of the best friend iâ’ve ever had.

title: Forever Leave a Mark

text: forever leave a mark  i've been laying here for so long,  thinking bout you and i/ i know it's hard to let this go,  but we'll be alright/ if pain can fade away,  it will dim tonight/ instead of saying goodbye,  iâ’ll just say goodnight/ oh i miss you babe/ but i know what we did was right/  we won't cry the tears we've cried on love anymore/ we will cast away the pain,  that we have held before/ we're gonna do whats best for you,  and whats best for me/ you look after yourself,  i'll look after me/ so now we'll depart/ and give up the spark/ but the love we shared will forever leave a mark/  i'll miss the way that we kissed,  made love,  and how i held you tight/  it's just love had rushed right into our hearts at the wrong time/ we laughed and we cried,  yeah we worked things out/ but we've sank so deep,  and there's no way out/ the only thing we should do now/ is live without/  we won't cry the tears we've cried on love anymore/ we will cast away the pain,  that we have held before/ we're gonna do whats best for you,  and whats best for me/ you look after yourself,  i'll look after me/ so now we'll depart/ and give up the spark/ but the love we shared will forever leave a mark/  one moment things might feel so right,  then the next they don't/ but nothing ever made me feel the way you do/  i'm so thankful to you baby for everything/ there are no regrets i swear for anything/ i think we gave it our best/ now we can lay our hearts to rest/  we won't cry the tears we've cried on love anymore/ we will cast away the pain,  that we have held before/ we're gonna do whats best for you,  and whats best for me/ you look after yourself,  i'll look after me/ so now we'll depart/ and give up the spark/ but the love we shared will forever leave a mark/

title: Coming up for air to calm down finally
author: christie
text: as i fell asleep one night i realized something very loud.   a beating drum,  or thumping bass.   it had no certain tempo.  seemed only like an increasing pace but maybe time was simply erased,  allowing no structure or planning anymore.   days no longer seem like twenty four hours.   i am lost in a firery uproar.   do i like or do i love?  do i mildly dislike this or do i loathe?  what is that noise?  where is it coming from and why can i not make it cease?  make it stop i implore. . .  i lay my head down to rest.   nothing though will allow me to shut my eyes,  nothing will allow me to ignore these signs.   signs and noises coming from my heart and head.   i knew it all along.   if i had only give attention to my selfish heart instead of being so selfless.   i could have taken a breath of fresh air.   oh how my feelings can not or will not repair themselves.   i will drown in this pool filled with thoughts of the stride of your walk,  the way you speak and/or talk, and especially how you dance.  yeah  i am longing to be with you and i realize why my heart beats this way and why i could not breathe while my face was turning a pale blue.   i realize i was thinking of something out of my reach,  exactly when thought i picked the peachiest peach.   i realize now i was thinking of you.

title: If walls could talk
author: christie
text: the special place is called my room.  i like to go there to sit,  sleep,  eat,  watch tv,  or just to think.  i like to go to my room so i can relax.   when i am in my room i like to write.  i write mostly about how my brother made me angry that day.  i hide my journal so no one can see it.  i like to keep my life private.   my room is where i go when i like to be by myself.  sometimes i just feel like getting away from everyone else.  i go in my room when i like to hide,  when i know something is wrong on the outside.   sometimes i go in my room when i am mad.  i slam the door and shut myself out from society.  i turn on the tv and forget about reality.   my room is my special place because i have had that space for eighteen years.  my room is my special place because itâ’s the only thing that knows all of my dreams and fears.  if walls could talk they would know everything about me.  my room is my special place because itâ’s my safe place to be.

title: Water Dance
author: christopher
text: tired i go,  go on in this violent desert,  who by its sands,  drain my life with every step,  with no sight of life around i cry out to the sky,  then rewarded by the sun's glare.   the sand begin to grasp at my legs,  begin to pull me toward my death,  with little strength i escape its grasp.  defeated,  i start to dance,  perhaps that it is from insanity,  but i dance for rain.   the sky responded,  with clouds it fills,  and it starts to pour,  pour its liquid sapphires up my frame.   yet i did not stop dancing,  for i was no longer there,  what was left was not me,  but a desperate creature who uses any way to get its needs,  a creature who took the form of a man,  in order to perform the water dance.

title: The Fight Within Me
author: christopher
text: maybe it was just the hand that i was dealt.   never had luck trying to figure life out.  i'm doing my best to be the best man i can be.   but there's something evil that dwells deep inside of me.   i'm cursed,  but i'm trying to be blessed.   every move i make seems to be a test.   the anxiety that sweeps over me can't be explained.  it's like a minefield inside my brain.  random thoughts just explode and fill me with pain.  when it rains it pours,   when it pours,   it rains.  the storm just brews like a hurricane.   it spins and swirls,  spirals and whirls.   my brain and my heart constantly quirll.   what's right seems wrong,   what's wrong seems right.   it's a daily battle,   and it gets worse at night.   i lie awake in bed fighting my thoughts,   trying to live right in a world full of wrong.  it's good vs evil.   angels vs demons,   god vs satan.   my hearts debating,   it's god i'm craving,   but a slave to satan.  it's money i'm chasing.   the ways of the world.   power and fortune.  you can keep the fame.   i wanna be rich   a man without a name.  but all at what cost?  eternal torture and pain?  in the fiery depths of hell scortching in flames? just so i can drive a porsche,  and own my own plane.   a mansion in the mountains,   a high rise in the sky,  a yacht that's for the ocean,   docked at a private island.  a bad chick for a wife,   super model style,   living the dream.   or so it seems,   but once i die,   what's it all mean? i can't take it with me.  it's now pointless it seems.   but what about a mansion in heaven?  the one promised to me.   with the streets of gold and no more agony. the pain is gone, happiness arrives.  people all perfect,  and eternally alive.  no more sickness, poverty, or hunger.  thru christ alone,  it  makes you wonder, why is it such a hard choice to make life is so short but we have no patience to wait.

title: Poems & Doors
author: christos
text: poems & doors… poetry is an enigmatic door and each poem is a different key helping us to unlock her.  thousands of keys have been written since today.   and millions of craftsmen are working on the keys of tomorrow and on the poems of the day after tomorrow.  poetry is a constant battle.  neither victory nor defeat.  the armada of poems stands still.  the guards on the walls wait.  nobody attacks.   perhaps poetry is the city that is never to be conquered,   or the door that is to remain forever locked…

title: Joy from the Rain

text: kindness is all i see when rain splashes down.  you are loyal to your word.  the call of the cracked earth you heard.  the parched ground,  turning dark brown as it drinks to the point of drowning.   the sound brings me peace,  not discord.  its music is pure the sound,  not blurred,   and its rejoicing brings you renown.   but the sound was once not so kind.  once mans' heart was quickened with fear,  his heart was hard,  his eyes blind.  but there was one man whose eyes were clear.  he alone was safe from your wrathful wind,  and when you remembered him,  he gave a cheer.

title: I am Wolf
author: colby
text: dancing rays of moonlight shine upon the water,  as softly padded steps travel slowly further.  the many howls that begin to pierce the starry night,  sound the call to the wolves to hunt and feast and fight.   playful growls erupt as the wolves begin to play,  others only think a moment before they jump into the fray.  laughter erupts among the pact as others sit and stare,  it seems that they are fighting but they're showing that they care.   the sun begins to rise and the wolves begin to sleep,  safely snuggled in their den as the sky begins to weep.  they wait upon the setting sun to exit from their lair,  at least this will give plenty time for the hunted to prepare.   out of all of this is only one thing you must know. . .  i am called the wolf,  this is truly so.

title: A New Day
author: colby
text: a new day dawns,  a new path revealed,  after the setting of the sun.  a haunted face,  a heart unhealed,  the loss of a loved one.   you take a breath,  you try to fight,  but sadness is what you feel.  a candle sputters,  it loses light,  darkness won't let you heal.   you wish to forget,  wish to fade,  tomorrow seems so far.  price to high,  a price you paid,  now this is who you are.   sadness,  anger,  fear,  frustration,  feeling that guide you away.  love and happiness are creation,  they won't lead you astray.   so don't lose hope,  don't lose your way,  the river carries on.  light will shine,  a glorious ray,  a beautiful and happy song.

title: Our Tiny Angels

text: on the day your daddy and i found out i was expecting was a miracle, then there was a second miracle, when the dr.  said there were two!we could hardly catch our breath!we were having a baby boy and a baby girl.  our life was going to be complete.  as we began preparing for the two of you our hearts and everyone around us was full of love and excitement waiting patiently for your arrival, waiting for the warmth and fullfillment a baby brings. i could feel your movement and hearyour heart beats, i'd tell you every day how much your daddy and i love you.  we will always tell you that, we will always be with you. but you were taken away from us so young, now we will never hear you say mommy, daddy, grandpa, grandma or even uncle. we will never hear your sweet voices say i love you mommy and daddy, never feel your small hands touch our faces, just know as they lay you to rest daddy and i and everyones lives you have touched love you and you will forever be in our hearts. most of all you will always be our miracles, our tiny angles.    love mommy and daddy

title: Crystalline Cascade
author: corbin
text: as it dips down over the rocky height,  it seems to turn into an immense cloud.  appearing almost still until it comes crashing down,  creating a harmonious white noise.  below,  it begins to calm.  transitioning into a turquoise glow.  surrounding,  verdant trees lie still allowing the fiery red sandstone to be their background.  the air smells fresh.  hints of rich soil along with the mellow aroma of minerals in the water.   this is my supreme paradise.  i savor the artistry of planet earth,  and at night,  the artist that is the infinity around it.  not dwelling over the future.  not dwelling over the past.  only existing in the immediate present.

title: Untitled
author: corey
text: i have no regrets,   only lessons to learn.  all this time,  i thought i found the one,  only to be fooled.  confusions shrouds the mind,  it grabs hold and wonâ’t relent.  treachery some call it,  heartache to others.   i know not where to go,  nor what to do.  iâ’m lost.  doubt seeps in.  was is true,  or just a hoax.  i see clearly now,  that little whisper,  that brainwashing influence,  settles in the depths.   no one knows,  how or why,  people change,  while loves stays the same.

title: Why We Dream
author: corey
text: in reality life is hard to live through.  that is why we dream.   we dream to escape the harsh reality around us,  we dream to become immortal and unafraid,  we dream to be happy and to get away from whatever isnâ’t,  we dream of memories both good and bad,  we dream to be heroes and do the impossible,  we dream of achieving honor and glory,  but most importantly when you dream remember one thing,  you dream to escape our world and enter your own.   in reality life will be hard.  and that is why we dream.

title: Digits

title: What Society Knew

title: I Wish You Cared

text: hello,  i'm daniel,  age 17.   i am using this poem for a 4h poetry club.   why have we all been put upon this sphere? did some malev'lent being mean us spite? were we left here to among ourselves fight and,  of our lord,  be in great awe and fear?  does he,  when looking down,  at us just leer? i think his grasp on us is far too tight or maybe the biblical texts were right,  and he is really just shedding a tear.   i think that god is merely being kind.  he gave us all we need in one small book.  it really is quite simple if we read.  he told us just to seek and we shall find.  all that we need to do is take a look,  and from our gleanings take his sovereign heed.

title: Where I'm From
author: daniel
text: i am from plane tickets and yellow cabs,  from home made apple pie.  i am from adventure and exploration.     i am from mango trees,  muddy trenches,  and home grown strawberries.    from the snow covered streets of canada to the hot and sandy hills of haiti,  from the jungles of guyana to the sweet home of farm.   i am from long walks through the woods,  i am from jim and merry and john and sally.  from one room classrooms and  â“no tv!â”   i am from very hot to sub-zero cold.  from cricket to long distance running.    from chicken curry,  corn on the cob,  and home made pizza.   missionaries to average joe.     i am from poisonous snakes coconut trees,  and stray packs of dogs.      from streets filled with kids,   to warm summer days.   i am from early morning breakfasts,  from tea time with grandma.   from sunday afternoon pinochle   to long tractor rides.    i am from long ago memories hidden by time,   books and books of travels covered with dust.   from loving and caring parents  who knew just what to say.     i am from untamed dreams of future plans,  from friendships lost amidst the change.     from chaos,  uncertainty,  and fear  to godâ’s perfect plan.    i am daniel m

title: Best Friends or Twin Brothers?
author: david
text: supposedly blood is thicker than water,  and somehow we come from the same mother and father.  he is supposed to be my best friend,  but it seems animosity is his latest trend.  he has been there for 18 years,  and has grown to learn of all my fears.  i would think he would understand,  but it seems even he doesn't comprehend.  now it appears, that he can't just hurt me,  and pretend there's nothing wrong.  especially when those feelings that hurt me,  are put into a song.  now we shall see,  exactly how he seems to me,  the brother i had for years,  that has begun to exploit my fears.

title: How Could You
author: david
text: how could you leave me when i have been searching for you my whole life?   how could you put a smile on my face then bring tears to me eyes?  how could you make me want to be with someone else after i told you that i wanted to be with you for the rest of my life?  how could you tell me that we are more than just friends when you act as if we are only associates?  how could you lie to me with a straight face when i asked you a question?  how could you steal from me when i gave you the world?  how could you get up and leave after some many years like you knew me for only a few days?  how could you tear my heart up in pieces when you are the one who made it whole?  how could you say you love me when your actions tell me a different story?  how could you warm up my day then treat me so cold?   how could you let me dream of us spending the rest of our lives together then shatter it by leaving?   how could you open the door to my heart then slam it right in my face?   how could you make me look foolish by telling you that i love you?   how could you think that my happiest moments were complete without you by my side?   how could you let me bear this pain of being lonely?   how could you steal from me when i gave you the world?   how could you leave me out here waiting for you to return?   how could you let me wait here with open arms wishing  to hold you,  but the only thing i am holding is air?      written by: david m.  w. -april 11, 2002-5:53p. m.

title: Secrets

text: laughter  filled the room when you sat next to me but,  no one knew but me we talked we listened we sat silently so close but yet so far but,   no one knew but me we politely said our goodbyes your eyes finally caught mine you even smiled at me right then,   i turned to leave it was best to leave but,   no one knew - but me.

title: FLAMES OF THE FOREST
author: davis
text: forest fire! flames everywhere,   birds flying away,  helter-skelter,   animals fleeing away for fear of death,   to places unknown yet safer for shelter.    small creeping crickets,  worms and snakes,   unable to keep pace with the flames,   consumed in the devastating fire,   turned into ashes,  dark and grey.    butterflies pretty and beautiful  yellow,  green,  maroon,  and black,   different colours,  designs and textures,   as if knitted and painted to perfection,   in a wee second succumbed to the sweltering heat.     what a sight! lonely,  disenchanting,  depressing,   soot covered tree trunks,  half-baked branches,   fully burned heaps of leaves and small bushes,   marked the forlorn landscape.    then i took a closer look,   death did not dominate the scene,   on the ground i could see the beginnings of new life,   thick undergrowth was beginning to take hold.   new roots,  new shoots,  new sprouts,  new leaves,   all from the ashes,  dark and grey,   no more the barren land,  forsaken by all,   â‘cause life cannot be defeated,  death is not the end.    new life has taken roots,   steady and prolonged rain did the magic.   let us celebrate the new life outside,   let us celebrate the new life within.     you cannot be consumed for all the time,   the raindrops of godâ’s love steady and prolonged,   will do the magic of restoring life.   rise from the ashes and become a new creation,   you shall never be consumed by the forest flame.

title: True Love
author: dawn
text: true love isn't old it's something quite new.   you can't go and seek it,  for it seeks you.   true love is invisible no one knows when it appears.  too many unusual things,  with so many fears.   true love is grand,  as long as we both understand,  no one can change it,  it's in both of our hands.   true love is honesty,  only among two.  when honesty grows,  the love then becomes true.

text: i saw her but i didnâ’t know what to say.   she saw me but she went about her way.   some day iâ’ll get the courage to make her my girl.   iâ’ll show her that i can give her the world.   iâ’ll protect her and keep her safe from harm.   and when sheâ’s cold iâ’ll hold her to keep her warm.   iâ’ll take her to have a good time.   and iâ’ll make sure she doesnâ’t spend a dime.   as good as this sounds and as good as it seems.   i have no courage so i must continue to dream

title: California Morning
author: deba
text: as  pallid cold morning breeze blows all around,  fallen autumn leaves strewn abound,  a vortex of wind picks them in its breath,  swirls them around in a dance of death.  cadaverous wind tempts me to step in,  embodied by it resonates the turmoil within.  it has a life of its own,  touching leaves that are dead,  leaves that are past their prime and no life ahead,  vivifying their listless existence for a moment,  alas,  just for an evanescent moment.  in this fleeting time,  does their hearts abound with joy really chime ? or,  is it me who is trying to find a spectre of life,  in this listless existence filled with strife.  or is it the melancholy mind ,  oblivious to the daily grind,  thinking too much ,  for the wind maybe doesnâ’t have any life as such.  or is the heart trying to find a resemblance,  to its tumultuous existence ,  its sangfroid core deathly calm and stolid with platitudes,  its shores beleaguered by the vicissitudes ? or is the vortex signifies lifeâ’s vacillations,  and the deep desire for reconciliation.  let the answers not be known,  let the thoughts be remain as a unanswered question,  for if the answers are uncovered,  the beauty of the thought would wither.

title: His Majesty
author: denis
text: poem 1 title: his majesty the ever shining star  of the greatest royal rocks of nkongho,  where always you stood tall,  his majesty tazanu njung-efuellah.  you are the rose of sharon,  and the lily of the valleys.  as the lily among thorns,  so is your love for your daughters.  as the apple tree among the trees of wood,  so is your care among your sons.    but,  years quickly have gone by,  the morning star steadily ceased,  to rise and pierce the dense woods of tock.  where have your majesty been? where are those glittering eyes,  which like the lion burst,  through the hearts of your subjects? where are those solemn words of wisdom,  which consoled the broken hearted and the poor in spirit?  has death with his cruel hands,  tricked you away? donâ’t tell me! donâ’t tell me! that you now rest,  where neither hopes,  nor fears,  nor joy rekindle your spirit.    njung-efuellah! havenâ’t you learnt,  no,  heard,  that from the north and west,  invaders have engulfed and walloped,   those hills and valleys of yours? your kingdom in captivity lies,  in the hands of aggressors.    day after day,  ceaseless springs,  down the chicks of your subjects,  like summer-melting snow run.  impotent and sluggishly,  your regency failed to stir fire in their hearts.  to stir this magnificent kingdom to resist cruel currents of captivity.     his majesty,  whereof the man,  that with us trod this soil,  was a napoleon,  emerging before the times were ripe.  that father,  comforter of ours who lives in the lord.  that the almighty,  which ever reigns and loves,  one god,  one word,  one spirit,  to which all creation drifts,  compensates him.     for,  â“where the word of the king is there is power: and who may say unto him,  what does thou?â”        poem 2 title: on the green hill submit               atungong step by step and gently i ascend the green hill hoping to step on the submit,  i rock,  twist and painfully pull upward,  to this spot all day long,  for,  from this point,  i long,   and i aspire to survive.   and to see fonki in its entirety,  i hope to continue,   so life can continue.     atungong! what a submit! the green hill submit.  behind at the heels of the hill,  and behind me lies fonki,  houses like dishes covered on table tops lie still,  with their silver caps.  footpaths like strings wind and meander between mush-room-like huts.    children like soldier-ants trace the strings to and fro,  while flog in the green vegetation faintly spotted,  like dots on plain sheet.  the calm sky filled with birds,  floating and singing happily from side to side and far at the horizon stand,  mounts like giants with green heads kissing the sky.     whistling sounds of insects compete with lovely melody of the joyful birds,  as foggy cloud slide gently from on high,   via gigantic forest wood above.    oh! atungong! my hope,  you make me see fonki,  from end to end and the land of seven rocks and beyond.   i toy and wail to arrive your top with kneels broken and tongue running out of my mouth.  while fine streams burst and run down my top to toe.  in fatigue like a hunting dog,  i pursue my course to the submit,  my hope.     alas! alas! at the submit: â“i have run my course i have fought a good fight i have kept the faithâ”   â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â—â— by denis

text: one time i was waiting at the airport to be called: destination was united states,   i saw my moms tears miles away but i couldn't  help my self to try and look away  i had to pick either leave or stay   leaving meant my mom stays behind  staying means i miss future opportunities  which way should i pick i think leaving will be best   leaving her behind was the worst mistake  i made,  only to not see her 3 years  after i came  should of picked staying instead if i  would of know it was going to be this way

title: THE WONDER OF A EYE
author: dennis
text: the wonder of an eye with shades of color round in shape and accompanied by another.   the wonder of an eye  to see in,  and it to gaze a portal,  clear and obscure sometimes confusing as a maze.    the wonder of an eye  reveals everything to occupy to look in and look out  to entertain and satisfy.    the wonder of an eye glints,  winks,  and squints a camera of magnificent design more priceless than a mint.    the wonder of an eye the mirror for the heart and mind communicates ideas of passion  for the earthbound and divine.    the wonder of an eye  dances and delights  rendering sparkles of light from romance to fright!

text: beautiful thoughts sew themselves stitch my stitch into my brain dissolving my thoughts of pain closing the wounds that once inhabited the space eventually,  the infection comes back to reek havoc my wounds rise to the surface worse than before invisible to the human eye,   yet apparent in the dimmest light of my soul the inflammation hurts as they continue to pour salt in my wounds spending precious time one by one in my heart dropping one grain of salt at a time only stopping to put thorns everywhere else the never-ending cycle is like an ocean,  i push them out only to let them back in maybe thatâ’s why people build an armor to keep the salt out  where is the happy medium?

title: Poem of beauty
author: diamond
text: beauty is not looking in the mirror everyday.  beauty is knowing that you're beautiful even when your not feeling your best.  beauty is what's on the inside not what's on the outside.  beauty is not putting on makeup everyday.  beauty is seeing you as you are and don't care what no one thinks.  beauty is nice long hair or short, glasses or no glasses,  ugly or not ugly,  whatever you are beautiful.

title: Corage
author: dickson
text: i stood there the place you left me.   a decade gone,  seasons passed before my eyes  without embracing me with its flavors as they do.   cold breeze never dared to break my solitude.   the closer we are in this messy world,   harder our hearts tried to speak in vain.   the longer you go away from where i stood.   hardened the fear of loss and death.   when came the uncertain times,   heart numbed to follow the unknown.   who says you are not good enough,   watch thy lies not spoil thy worth.

title: HOLIDAZE
author: dom
text: goodies in sox,  holiday cheer:  to your liking? likely no.   wind's 'a nipping,  christmas is near.   all seems merry.  look some more.    sky bent prices,  lists to fill.  gladsome smile as back slap flies.   gird-locked shoppers,  sweets to kill.   yet those sullen,  lifeless eyes.    something's missing.  brain's a fright.   might it be that in the muddle,    all's jolly: no joy's in sight.        grab yourself and have a huddle.       din and garbled,  `days of yore,  ma and pie, ' the ads ring out.   leave you wondering,  ''who's it for?''         trees and stores glitter to shout.     show your heels while you still might,    lest your being takes a rout.         don't buy trash.  put up a flight.          chill! jack frost turned 'lil christ out.

title: To absent thoughts
author: don
text: absent thoughts.  i use to know this landscape so well, as far as the eye can see.  but not now, gaps have appeared, connections lost, shortcuts missing.  i go the long way around,  but i forget why,  and what for.  thoughts,  a street of demolished houses,  now empty spaces,  like rotting teeth in a gummy grin.  i use to make that jump easily, but now its to wide, a bottomless pit.  signposts point the wrong way, a wasted journey of time and effort.  memories now just broken mirrors, a missing jigsaw picture a lucky dip of names without faces, or faces without. . . .  billy!?. . .  bits and peices, numbers, words, broken songs.  who are you again ?i wooden beams,  creaking and straining to hold up an attic of, ''what's this!?'' things.  something use to go here. . . a. . ? rooms of clutter and scattered paper trails to. . ? important things gathering dust, and i don't know why.  what day is this ?.

title: She's....Different
author: durane
text: she's. . . different the apple to my unseen eye where i cant stop to look,  but always stop to think how my life would be different if she had chosen me,  i drip pain from my eyes as my eyes seem to see the scene being chopped and screwed like in a dream.  but i dream not its just the fact i never see her much as i clutch down to earth seeing this angel hit the turf,  my worst thought is that she will be happy,  seeing smiles decorate the inscriptions put up onto her face.  why it cant be me. . . god only knows that,  as i seem as though i would be the perfect king to the queen of that throne,  my tone has taken a turn for the worst as my only moments of us has scarred me to state of no return,  the burn has paralyzed my secrets and tendered my soul cuz even whole parts of my body freeze up when i see her again.  as friends we hit it off,  we both wanted to proceed and succeed into the future,  never then looking back.  then it changed,  and it never seems to do me any better,  cuz the weather of the storm has placed me in a form of. . .  incomplete.   i meet her days later snuggled up in a love-like type trance mistaken for a lust-like type trance,  my heart seems to boil in my stomach as my eyes pain to look,  my ears seem to poison as her giggles are oblivious and her smile seems to shine.  my welcome has been worn.  my heart has been torn.  my thoughts have been scorned,  and a new life is born.  hatred has cascaded and faded off to black,  i blind my visions now,  cuz my eyes hit the ground,  and even though i hate her,  i never will forget.  and when i think back to place her in my past,  all i can say is. . .  she's different. . .

title: My true love Thomas
author: dustin
text: my love for you is like a river and the sound of a drum beating like my heart.  you are my soulmate my everythink my knight in shinning armor,  my divine lover my future husband.  your voice is so hipnotizing force you put me in a trance-you are such a good looking man i'm am very happy to have you as my boyfriend,  your smile lights up my world and you send my soul on a journey.  i care for you and my love for you is everlasting and meaningfull you give me so much joy and you make me happy ,  i love you thomas.

title: Maggie
author: earlene
text: maggie maggie with her soulful brown eyes looks at you with bountiful insight.   she loves to play for days and days and stops only to pace away.   her favorite toy is the round and yellow she wants it tossed across mellow meadow.   off she gallops a mile a minute and jumps sky high to catch it.    when the days it long been gone maggie sits close by all night long.    maggieâ’s love is unconditional true as any dog that is traditional.

title: Life
author: ebunoluwa
text: what makes life different from strife? life is made up of crises full of trouble that arises every time with its fantasies  life is full of treasures owned by nature but without great gesture,  how are we going to make an adventure into lifes future  lifes made up of different texture and structure which does not desire any pleasure but must be a measure  to problems of different mixtures   its up to us to know lifes estimable value,  its worth and troth we must capture lifes treasures then,  life would be a better place for all.

title: SUCCESS
author: ebunoluwa
text: success is a process though it involves losses it is full of goods with different prices which can result into a lasting legacy  success is made up of broken pieces put together by the auspices of great destinies carved out of lifes property filled with liberty and prosperity  success is a surety it helps to pacify and modify  the agony of failure and also the adversary of lifes mystery  success implies hard work so,  we all have to stand up to make a worth out of our uncountable falls then,  we would definitely have a different story,  with a greater glory.

title: Chelsea

title: If my pet could talk
author: eden
text: my nose is wet  my feet are big i stay by your side everyday and every step of the way.  i am always there to cudle when you feel sick or when you just are laying in bed i will alway greet you at the door because i know you will always come home.  you rub my tummy and give me baths even though i run and hide you are always there to talk to me in that baby voice i dont quite understand and after you brush my fur and take me for a walk.  an you say i am good and sweet girl you sit on the floor with me just so i dont feel left out for not being able to get on the coach.  i just love being your friend you treat me very very well.

title: Our Presidents - From George W. to George W.
author: edwin
text: one  george washington (1732-1799) served as president between 1789 and 1797  an extraordinary general,  a man whose life would end,  had the war he fought with england failed to properly defend â– the rights of all americans to say whatâ’s on their minds.  a favorite of many: â“the best weâ’ve had so far.  heâ’s greater than the others â– make that â‘all the rest combined. â’â”  two  john adams (1735-1826) served as president between 1797 and 1801  braintree massachusetts was the home to this brave man.  yet many years were spent away in european lands.  the nation needed money,  to kick the english out,  so off to france and amsterdam with far more hope than doubt.  this massachusetts lawyer,  with skills and smarts galore,  returned across atlanticâ’s sea with cash that won the war.   three   thomas jefferson (1743-1826) served as president between 1801 and 1809  from a plantation in virginia,  with his hair a copper-red,  this shy man wrote more brilliant words than he had ever said.  a farmer,  an inventor too,  he took his pen and ink,  declaring independence from george,  the english king.   four  james madison (1751-1836) served as president between 1809 and 1817  like jefferson and adams,  a man of brilliant words,  known to folks across the world â– theyâ’re read,  theyâ’re spoke,  theyâ’re heard.  he wrote our constitution which gives us guarantees â– that laws and just decisions would keep our people free.   five  james monroe (1758-1831) served as president between 1817 and 1825  this lawyer from virginia as a soldier in the war,  he fought the english redcoats,  and as president did more: he kept out europeâ’s tyrants,  forever from the shores of nearby south america â– preventing further wars.   six  john quincy adams (1767-1848) served as president between 1825 and 1829  for years right by his fatherâ’s side,  while america was formed.  he lived the ways of service â– since to patriots he was born.  he spent hard years as president like most â– but then when done,  he ran and served in congress till his last days in the sun.    seven  andrew jackson (1767-1845) served as president between 1829 and 1837  a famous western general from our second english war â– the one we call â“the eighteen twelveâ” â– in new orleans andy scored.  and when he was the president,  he let the public in to party at the white house â– like some raucous roadside inn.   eight  martin van buren (1782-1862) served as president between 1837 and 1841  like adams he served just one term,  some said â“on jacksonâ’s tails. â” his famous home â– â“old kinderhookâ” changed â“yesâ” from here to wales.  see â– every time we say â“o. k. â” we abbreviate the name of van burenâ’s home near albany â– thatâ’s martinâ’s claim to fame…!!!  nine  william henry harrison (1773-1841) served as president between march 1841 and april of 1841  this general from virginia,  fought indians and earned the name â– â“tippecanoeâ” from the creek nearby,  where a victory brought him fame.  sadly though,  he caught a cold,  then he up-and-died,  just days beyond his swearing-in â– his white house job untried.    ten  john tyler (1790-1862) served as president between 1841 and 1845  a man of strong convictions,  the kind that fueled the hate â– between the folks of north and south and the war between the states.  the only former president,  who joined the rebelsâ’cause,  by serving in their congress â– where confederates made their laws.   eleven  james polk (1795-1849) served as president between 1845-1849  if you had to pick a president with a knack for adding states,  heâ’s near the lead â– like jefferson â– but not what youâ’d call â“great. â” said he: â“â’been governor from out in tennessee,  but white house work is way too tough â– one termâ’s enough for me. . !â”  twelve  zachary taylor (1784-1850) served as president between 1849-1850  another virginia general,  and hero of the mexican war,  the whigs said: â“please be president, â” old zack said,  â“why â– what for? iâ’ve never even voted,  â‘bout that iâ’ve never lied. â” he won of course,  but got real sick,  and shortly â– old zack died.    thirteen  millard fillmore (1800-1874) served as president between 1850-1853  poor millard â–he was vee pee when president twelve went dead,  that made him number thirteen (a number some folks dread. ) so whatâ’s his contribution,  since his white house time werenâ’t much? itâ’s indoor pipes where water flowed,  and toilets they could flush.   fourteen  franklin pierce (1804-1869) served as president between 1853-1857  this native of new hampshire,  while many thought quite bright,  made piles of poor decisions,  that just plain werenâ’t too right.  when fighting broke in kansas,  with farmers getting killed,  pierce wouldnâ’t send out soldiers,  and folks thought: â“heâ’s bad news. â”  fifteen  james buchanan (1791-1868) served as president between 1857-1861  a man of pennsylvania,  and single all his life,  his niece â– she played first lady and acted like a wife.  hot talk of war was brewing,  but buchanan seemed to feel: â“our nation can survive such talk,  if not â– itâ’s no big deal. â”     sixteen  abraham lincoln (1809-1865) served as president between 1861-1865  so tall in size,  so great was he,  this kind man from the plains: â“the unionâ’s saved,  the slaves â‘been freed,  though blood of soldiers stain those silent fields where armies fought,  that liberty â– remains. â”  seventeen  andrew johnson (1808-1875) served as president between 1865-1869  this senator from tennessee,  (a union man they said) became our nationâ’s president,  with lincoln shot â– and dead.  the congress said,   â“youâ’re awful! get out â– youâ’re just a pain! you never wouldâ’ve had the job had lincoln not been slain!â”  eighteen  ulysses s.  grant (1800-1874) served as president between 1869-1877  itâ’s said this famous general won our civil war,  by giving southern soldiers their dignity - and more: he said: â“boys,  take your horses,  go home and live there free. â” grant even showed great kindness to the rebel general â– lee.      nineteen  rutherford b.  hayes (1822-1893) served as president between 1877-1881  â“iâ’ll only serve but one full term,  like every president should. â” but many scowled and even said,  â“hayes couldnâ’t if he would.  besides we chose that other guy â– we liked him,  heâ’s real good. â” itâ’s true,  in fact â– that hayes had lost by tons of votes that year,  but laws allowed that congress had the right to interfere.   twenty  james garfield (1831-1881) served as president between march 1881 and september of 1881  like harrison and taylor too,  whose terms were both cut short,  this president â– he up and died,  twice shot â– by a crazy sort.  a general in the civil war,  just forty-nine years old,  he dodged the shots from rebel guns,  but this guy got him â– cold.   twenty-one  chester a.  arthur (1829-1886) served as president between 1881-1885  born to an irish preacher,  chester loved to look his best: â“he likes to change his pants a lot. â” â“heâ’s president best dressed. â” a champion of the laws we have for doing government work: â“no longer will you lose your job on whims of elected jerks. â”  twenty-two  grover cleveland (1837-1908) served as president between 1885-1889  so far,  of all our presidents,  this guyâ’s the only one,  who served two terms but split â‘em up â‘tween a one-term â‘publican.  a bachelor â– came he to the white house,  then fell for a good palâ’s kid,  and brought her back from buffalo,  to marry â– which is what they did.   twenty-three  benjamin harrison (1833-1901) served as president between 1889-1893  the last of the civil war generals,  his grandpa was president too.  his term â– it brought some milestones â– like six states added new,  and nature â– showed her cruelties,  though menâ’s were worse to see â– those hundreds drowned in johnstownâ’s flood,  were no-match for wounded knee.   twenty-four  grover cleveland (1837-1908)  served again as president between 1893 and 1897  remember grover cleveland â– the guy with two split terms. . ?? his second was a nightmare â– crises â– what a can of worms. . !! his mouth â– it needed surgery: so they fixed him â– on a boat,  his new jaw was kept secret,  alongside: â“ladies should not vote. â”  twenty-five  william mckinley (1843-1901) served as president between 1897 and 1901  americans loved the twenty-fifth,  as much as america could.  the war with spain was fought and won,  though he had said: â“we should â– not wage war where peace will do,  theyâ’ve done us little harm. â” his last stop â– that was buffalo,  where mckinley â“bought the farm. â”  twenty-six  theodore roosevelt (1858-1919) served as president between 1901 and 1909  the youngest of our presidents,  he loved to be outside,  the giant parks we have out west â– were teddyâ’s joy and pride.  his face looks out from rushmoreâ’s mount,  with greats of awesome fame â– presidents who risked it all,  (somehow â– heâ’s not the same. )  twenty-seven  william howard taft (1857-1930)  served as president between 1909 and 1913  the largest of our presidents,  he walked a leaderâ’s path.  but when he won the white house,  he couldnâ’t fit the bath.  more jobs had taft than he could count: â“iâ’ve done it all â– it seems,  supreme court judge and cabinet jobs,  i ran the philippines. â”     twenty-eight  woodrow wilson (1856-1924) served as president between 1913 and 1921  a solemn man â–a preacherâ’s son: â“iâ’ll not send boys to war. â” but troops did sail â– his second term,  to a far-off foreign shore.  our soldiers fought the kaiserâ’s men,  and in the end we won,  though wilsonâ’s dream of world-wide peace has yet to be â– not done.   twenty-nine  warren harding (1865-1923) served as president between 1921 and 1923  there were those who said that harding got elected on his looks: â“his face â– itâ’s presidential, â” but thatâ’s hardly what it took: he proudly stood for suffrage,  (which means that ladies vote) and when he was a newsman,  folks admired what he wrote.   thirty  calvin coolidge (1872-1933) served as president between 1923 and 1929  the sixth time that a president got tapped because of death,  was vermont son â– cal coolidge (a job weâ’re told he dread).  a thoughtful man â– heâ’d only say exactly what he should,  â“silent calâ” â– they called him and they knew right where he stood.       thirty-one  herbert hoover (1874-1964) served as president between 1929 and 1933  a geologist and a genius type,  devoted to the poor,  but once he earned the white house job,  more got poor â– for sure.  â“he busted our economy, â” so many people said: â“weâ’ve got no jobs. â” â“our homes are gone. â” â“we live in cardboard sheds. â”  thirty-two  franklin delano roosevelt (1882-1945)  served as president between 1929 and 1945  a charming man â– some said had airs: â“itâ’s that funny way he talks. â” four times we chose him president,  (few knew he couldnâ’t walk).  the cruelest war in history,  the whole world now admits,  (â“our greatest fear is fear itselfâ”) was won by this manâ’s wits.   thirty-three  harry s.  truman (1884-1972) served as president between 1945 and 1953  said this senator of missouri: â“i love this job way-much. â” the dems begged,  â“please be vee pee. â” â“no,  iâ’ll be too out of touch. â” he got the job,  three months passed by,  our prez went off to heaven: â“â’seems iâ’m like six veeps before,  that makes me lucky seven. â”   thirty-four  dwight d.  eisenhower (1890-1969)  served as president between 1953 and 1961  a general who in world war two,  became this nationâ’s hero,  was sure to become president: (folks even bet dinero!) â“a college job â– thatâ’s fine for me â– wonâ’t run for no oneâ’s party. â” but ran he did and served two terms,  which left him less-than-hearty.   thirty-five  john f.  kennedy (1917-1963) served as president between 1961 and 1963  his speeches filled our hearts with hope,  the world â– it shed great tears,  when bullets took this president of forty-plus-six years.  a man of faith who loved to sail in cape codâ’s chilly waters,  stood up against a russian threat to harm our sons and daughters.   thirty-six  lyndon baines johnson (1908-1973)  served as president between 1963 and 1969  the eighth vee pee to take the oath,  in a plane at dallas airport,  never planned on white house work: â“jackâ’s young and wonâ’t be cut short. â” a clever man who knew the ways of congress and d. c. ,  drove through laws where civil rights to all were guaranteed.     thirty-seven  richard m.  nixon (1913-1994) served as president between 1969 and 1974  nixon went to
