title: Life's Lookin Up
author: elisabeth
text: the dark can consume many of people's hopes and dreams nothing good can come of the future days ahead days drag into weeks,  years,  and an eternity it seems before the dark claims the dead  but there is a light there,  a glimpse of a day promised a day where everything is and will be as it should this day will be the best,  to even be called glorious no crying,  no pain for good  come quickly my heart cries out to the one and only i just can not live any longer here though i must all the people i will see when i'm there,  never lonely  til that day,  in you i trust  i find that because of you my life is worth living you are my rock,  my salvation til the very end i know that through all of the trials i must keep believing you are my now and my then  these days might seem to be gloomy and overwhelming these days filled with hurt,  depression,  and brutality but just remember that the light at the end is coming  soon to be reality

title: Dreams
author: elizabeth
text: dreams belong to everyone.  thet are fragments of reality you see.  no matter if they are good or bad,   they are part of you and me  sometimes they try and tell us,  how our plans are going wrong.  sometimes they just remind us where our hearts do not belong.   at times we dream of castles and land  both near ad far.  of knights in shinning armor,  or just wishing on a star.   dreams are a part of life,  i know they are what they are.  but wouldn't it be nice,  if we could dream all good dreams and save them in a jar.

title: The pain of loosing someone
author: emily
text: you left me in the rain with hurt and pain,   no words to say but tears running down my face.  i knew you never loved me,  i knew you never cared,  but somehow i thought you would always be there.   i thought you would be there when i cry,  i thought you would be there when i nearly died.   but i was wrong and i have still have them lyrics of our song,   our song have so many memories,  of us kissing in the snow and the time we as singing hi ho.  and now i'm missing you even though it has only been a second.  i love you.

title: No more
author: emily
text: behind these shades hide a pain that only she feels underneath the concealer,  eyeliner foundation,  face powder is the face of a person fed up tired of being ridiculed,  picked on fed up of being the scapegoat,  the guinea pig the go to girl.   under the black nail polish and loud music is a depression so severe,  it has no cure is an agony so intense,  it shatters her very being an affliction so real,  it seems fake  a girl tired tired of being the one with the world on her shoulders tired of smiling and nodding to appease the other tired of being unwanted when being wanted is all she ever wants  sheâ’s sick of holding in the tears that seem to want to burst forth out of her like a dam,  like an overflowing river sick of not having an opinion an option,  a choice to say what she feels yet is still encouraged to do it sheâ’s sick of bowing her head and letting people spit hurtful words at her words that threaten to destroy her very being words that have already destroyed her psyche  no more… no more walking all over me and me not saying a thing about it no more not letting me have a voice no more making me feel like iâ’m inferior to you making me feel like you are better than me  no more taking me for a fool and playing me like a clever game of chess no more standing on my back breaking me so that i can boost you up  no more relying on me to finish things that can be accomplished by you.  no more yesâ’s no more okays no more of course i donâ’t mind  i will take no more hate me,  talk about me secretly but you will never,  not ever again make me feel like iâ’m no more.

title: Haikus
author: emily
text: yellow boots tread through puddles rain plummets from foggy gray skies droplets collect on the tip of my nose i hope the sun will come out soon  children hang from branches  underneath green canopies  laughing at their adventure   misty waters slow my travel  lost between the stars i must wait until tomorrow.

title: When I first Set Eyes on Her
author: emily
text: when i first set eyes on quest,  i imagined a mountain,  with beauty in her eyes,  she looked at me,   and i looked shyly away,  and i instantly fell in love,  but was afaid to get on,  i could ride the schooling horses,  no doubt about that,  but she was so tall,  what would happen if i fall,  all all all the way down? whould it hurt,  of course,  so big,  so gently,  and not her fault,  that she was so big,  i tickled her nose through the stall door,  and said what a nice day for a ride -  she nickered in agreement,  the owner said i could ride her,  i was good enough after all,  but should i do it? should i? she gave me a leg up,  and i looked at the ants below,  they called up edvide,  and i then knew,  i need this horse,  and thats how the forever ride started:)

title: Fallen Friend
author: eric
text: an ode to my fallen friend                                                   eric arries every day is not the same without you; there is something missing inside me.  i wish everyday that you were here; so that i can share life with you.  deep inside i know it is impossible; but yet,  my feelings i hide.  you have trodden deep tracks in my heart; some days i search for your tracks on the sand; but realise itâ’s been wiped.  wiped by time- you always had a phrase: time will tell! and yet i wait for time; to alleviate the pain.   but the wait is in vain.  until we meet again your friend.  e -(nd).

title: As I Sleep
author: erica
text: as i sleep  i dream of you & me when i wake itâ’s you iâ’ll see i let you fly free like bird  but i know you would come back home.  as i sleep the day away  i know itâ’s you i pray when i wake itâ’s you iâ’ll say iâ’ll see you the next day.  as i sleep i dream of you & me my heart skips a bet  are love shines through? so that everyone can see we stand as one with open arms  your voice mellows me out.  thatâ’s how i sleep…  but to know you is a blessing from above to be with you is a blessing a lone  for you to have me is a blessing from god   this is the love that shines through it all…    love,          erica r

title: Deeper Passions
author: erica
text: searching for passion hidden somewhere  by electric abstractions.  find me if you dare.  a delicate song,  fragile wonderment tune breaks over the river in a beautiful bloom.  don't overlook dewdrops or ignore springtime song,  you'll hear a voice whisper ''though small i am strong. '' dive into the moment,  deeper passions you'll find.  future memories guide you leaving midnight behind.  so follow the river as it tumbles and falls.  you'll hear harmonies melting as the melody calls.  golden hues touch the sunset as the brightest night flees.  deeper passions are rising.  you are finally free.

title: The Forest
author: erin
text: it's lonely in the forest of my mind,   mosquitoes chew my eyes till i'm half blind,   i'll give you my arm until it rips,   if only to taste the sicily spices on your lips,   so throw me in a ditch and tan my hide,   till i see spirits from the other side,   i don't need anyone else but you,   and i'll remain yours till i turn blue,   we'll drink any milk that we can find,   you can play rough and i won't mind,   if the clouds roll in to rain on my desire,   we'll get some sticks and start a fire,   the fog blocks out the moon's pale,  glowing shine,    but i don't need it because you are so fine,   if i could feel your precious breath on me,   my heart would sing a melody,   in the forest of my mind.

title: Water in the Hall
author: erin
text: don't stew in your loneliness and your increasing sins,   you came out of the tub but it has flooded over,   pieces of broken remnants have clogged the drain,   water spills over the side and into the hall,   washing away the dreams you have dreamed,   rising through the steam are ideas,   the ideas of what might have been,   they glistened on the mirror which has become misty,   how i long to pinch and feel you,   and experience the glory of your appetizing skin,   so think of me while standing on your head,   i will think of you for the rest of my life,   the water you have bathed in runs across the floor,   and i would sip the water in the hall,   just to have the taste of you,   i won't let your water run down the abyss of the staircase,   each little drop is one you have used,   i won't let your dreams be washed away,   i'll grab a towel and dry up the water,   a part of you will then be safe,   and no longer be water in the hall.

title: Halloween Night
author: erin
text: there would be no need to dress up if you came to our door,   because you're unspeakably handsome right down to the core,   if you came trick-or-treating,  i'd let you enter with a key,   but you're a savage; you bring out the devil in me,   there is one thing i'd give you besides a bag of candy,   and that's a slice of pie,  freshly baked and dandy,   the folks have left no cider for you to drink,   but it's typical; they never really stopped to think,   so brush the wool away from your eyes,   and see how the holiday season lies,   ahead of all the sweat and time it takes to push the grind,   whether you come here for candy or not,   i'll always be waiting and stirring the witch pot,   for there's a time and a place for all that is keen,   that place is here,  and the time is halloween,   now it's time to take the pumpkin off your head,   throw it in the fridge,  and come to bed,   but the spiders come; thankfully they have already fed,   the smell of your flesh is sweeter than meat,   i'm no cannibal,  but you seem good enough to eat,   you goblin,  how else could i feel?  i'm ignoring the monster in the closet and his pet electric eel,   nothing about you is just a phase,   you're the one i love for now and always,   happy halloween.

title: Him
author: erum
text: lot of time has passed now waiting for the one,  whose arrival seems to be coming soon.   bright sunny mornings keep my warmth alive,  and though i've struggled for love,  i know i'm gonna get it right.   unparallel life makes me feel,  that its all gonnna be worth the wait.   its hard not knowing who he is but i still keep dreaming in optimism,  that one day he'll arrive,  the day when my dreams will blossom.   i hope he's just as crazy as i am,  or maybe a little more,  the kind of crazy that i haven't seen ever before.   the kind of protective like my dad,  the sort of a best friend that i have.   some silly innocence is what i wanna see in his eyes.  and feel in my stomach,  flying butterflies.   aaah. .  where are you my mr.  perfect,  my dude? i'm waiting here all alone writing this for you!

title: My Tears
author: erum
text: tears,  yes they are important,  so i shed them day and night,  after winning and losing,  after every fight.  these tears explain that i feel it all,  that i stumble and fall,  i walk and i crawl.  i cry and scream but there's nobody to listen,  that i'm dying and that my heart is broken.  and now the broken pieces of my heart can't be brought together,  now its something that's gone forever.  everything shattered before my eyes and i was helpless like a little kid,  all i did was shed my tears and had a feeling that i wasn't fit.  wasn't fit for what i admire.  wasn't fit for what i desire.  wasn't good enough to make people feel  that i have feelings too and they are all for real.  but i'm helpless before their tiny little brains,  their zipless mouth that always blames.  blames me and only me for everything wrong,  they're taking me away from the place i belong.  so all i did was shed my tears,  and realised that i had to get over my fears.  i can't do it all alone though,  i need some support,  but these people only know how to drown my boat.  what have i done so wrong that you all judge me all the time? is loving someone and living for my dreams really a crime? if that's what it is then hang me i'd love to die.  just make sure that my soul is taken away before my tears dry!

title: Golden Gate Bridge
author: faith
text: i look down; the water seems farther from up here.  i think of my family; why didn't my mom call me yesterday? my life consists of work,  and like the bills,  itâ’s never ending i just want a break,  i want it to stop.   the woman to my left is saying something to me; i donâ’t understand her,  sheâ’s distant.  the girl to my right stares at me,  like iâ’m not human.  she doesn't think i will do it,  but i will.    iâ’m wearing a red hoodie,  jeans,  and flip-flops.  nothing about me screams â“helpâ” like i wish it would.   there must be others on this bridge that look to the city,  wishing to fly.  i wonder what my mom would say if she knew i needed her all along.    the golden gate bridge has always been there for me i can see her from work; sheâ’s beautiful.  sheâ’s been a symbol of adventure,  of life! itâ’s only fitting that she should be there when i say goodbye.    i keep muttering something to the woman on my right â“just one more answerâ” i mumble i think back,  i've lived my life this way,  this will be my last answer.    i slowly lean forward; this is the point of no return.  gravity pulls me down slowly,  yet the water comes too quick.  â“the life of mortals is like grassâ” rings too true.  i regret not saying goodbye to mom.

title: TALL PEOPLE
author: fran
text: tall people  when we were little,  the â“tallâ” people took good care of us.  they changed our diapers,  cleaned our noses; listened to us fuss.  they protected us; they watched us grow; they cried when we cried.  they hoped and prayed we wouldnâ’t try the things that they had tried.   the â“tallâ” people bandaged our wounds and nursed us back to health.  they believed that having us was more precious than having wealth.  they wanted to fight our battles,  although they knew they shouldnâ’t.  they did for us all the things we wanted to do,  but couldnâ’t.   the â“tallâ”  people,  as we grew older,  had to let go a little more.  the sleepless nights seemed to get longer as they waited and walked the floor.  they wanted to trust us; they wanted to let go.   they knew we had to fly.  we got angry; we wanted freedom; we wanted to know â“why. â”  one day we realized the â“tallâ” people werenâ’t really all that tall.  we no longer had to look up; in fact,  they looked awfully small.  we now looked up in a different way,  with love and trust and respect.  the â“tallâ” people smiled with tears in their eyes for a gift they didnâ’t expect.

title: Pear Tooth
author: gina
text: when i awoke one morning,  a stork was on my bed.  i asked ''what are you doing there?'' it looked at me and said. . . .   ''i'm the new tooth fairy but i seem to have lost my way.  i'm supposed to get the tooth from where a pear lays. ''  i thought for a minute and so did the bird,  ''a tooth of a pear? are you sure you have the right word?''  the stork was very sure,  ''we can find it in the woods! i have some instructions and a jar of pear food. ''  the jar was full of meat and that really made no sense! but the pear was in the woods so this is where we went.   ''it says we must be careful cuz a pear can sometimes bite. '' i showed the stork my muscles and said,  ''not without a fight!''  but i was kind of nervous because i never fought a fruit.  and i really had no weapon except a sliver from a root.   and what if it had friends. . . .  what am i talking about?! ''pears don't bite!'' i started to shout.   ''ssssshhhhh!'',  the stork warned,  ''it's asleep in that cave. '' we walked into the opening,  trying to be brave.   ''i think i see it sleeping,  it's laying right there!'' it looked where he was pointing and saw. . . . . . .  a great big bear!!  the stork was very careful as he lifted the bears head,  and found a little tooth and then tucked him back in bed.   when we left the cave,  the stork - that silly goof -  opened up his hand and showed me the ''pear tooth''.

title: Damage Control
author: hannah
text: when we hear about a new school shooting,  we collectively gasp,  before turning our faces back to our work.  because itâ’s easier to solve geometryâ’s problems than the nationâ’s.  we ignore the cracks in our own concrete walls,  pretending that each mile between our school and an elementary in california is another mile of bulletproof glass.  we pretend we are untouchable,  and that the faces of shattered mothers and their blood soaked babies could never be our own.  we see body bags zip away the corpses of children on the news,  never realizing that the scene doesnâ’t fade away when we change the channel.  instead,  we learn to focus on the things that donâ’t matter.  we care about making varsity,  not letting the pasta burn to the bottom of the pan.  forgetting to lock our cars twice,  and drinking our beers without coasters underneath them.  we cry when we fall off our bikes,  and again when we run out of band aids.  we donâ’t think about the people who lost their lives unless we have to,  because the parallels between them and us are far too similar,  and itâ’s easier to sleep at night when tragedies are just stories.

title: The Chameleon
author: helen
text: why must my soul adjourn to the meek and weary lighthouse in the sky? not of heaven or of any ethereal light,  but of the unpromising tabernacles that endure even the slightest bit of a clown's inwardly chuckle.    why must a bard in his wise array of words feel the desolate insubordination of a lone wolf who neither preaches nor expects one to comprehend his howl?   shall i resort to a presence upon more compelling grounds? perhaps the limelight of a learner's paradise,  pose as a student and forget the rage of the modern price?   apologies grow short for all the parties that it may involve.  take a look at the way a butterfly's flap may stir a ruthless,  preeminent storm  the way a dying king may identify with his gentle,  yet sovereign throne.    and if anything,  i've concluded for the sake of my inner peace: though i may be no martyr,  no mockingbird,  nor heroine,  i  bring harm only to those who view my acts as more than self-righteous folly.    don't scold a victim if you don't wish for your ignorance to show.  don't fight a system if it's uncharted within the realms you know.    if you don't hear me,  then hold your lobes.  if my spirit does not please you,  then go join the rest of your methodological revolution.  please don't mind me as i snicker at your fallen ship and watch as you wipe away the tears shed from the plasma of your pragmatic whisk.    i've seen no macabre but the very demons that plague me.  i've felt no pain but the pain that mercy feeds me.  some may see me as the eternal hoax,  a serpent,  a fool,  a rust-covered tool.  raving wildly over points seemingly incomprehensible to the mindful mindlessness of such an idiosyncratic generation.    don't mock my style,  don't mock my words.  your disdain is  as weak as the havoc i supposedly wreak.   i warn you to not attempt to even lift a finger in effort to crush an already battered psyche.    live your life according to the dreams you've dreamt as a child; entwine it with the lust you've felt as a man and see how it sprouts from there.    i claim to be a fallible preacher,  but who isn't in days of such gloomy weather? name someone who seems to be ''put together'' and then we'll turn this table around and perhaps battle like legends in the illustrious western sundown.

title: Beauty is all I see
author: hosneara
text: every day goes by,  like how the sun rises from beneath and set from above.  i can feel the breeze right through me.  itâ’s as if iâ’m hallow from the inside.  i dream of big things.  of becoming independent,   to be free to travel the world.   i hope for peace and love.  i remember back than it wasnâ’t easy to see the world,  locked in a cage.  rules and expectations are what i had to follow.  breaking out i have opened up,  my love for curiosity made me no longer wonder,  what is behind the walls that once guarded me.  i found the keys to open it,  they were with my mother,  overprotective is her name.  i guess all i had to do is have the courage to stand up in front of her,  to be who i want to be,  i tell her what i strive for is far more difficult to reach then the past.  with strength comes courage.  with difficult memories comes a sun full of serendipity.  i have to remind myself that there is hope,  right here,  on the palm of my hand is where i trust my heart to lay,  the lines that cross and intersect,  holds my future,  if you can read it donâ’t tell me,  a surprise is always better than expectations.  i tell her like many i have insecurities to,  so i throw away my thoughts,  replacing them with quotes,   poems,  and advice.  that opens up my mind to another world of familiarity.  i tell her i need confidence.  if i can plant a seed every time i had a happy day,  iâ’d build a forest,  flowers blossoming nature takes its course.  when disaster hits come a rainbow.  maybe if i was patient enough id see a pot of gold.  instead,  i stare take it all in.  beauty is all i see.

text: i broke my face yesterday and it hurt baseball hit me as hard as a brick wall it had me face down in the red dirt my face no longer looks like a ken doll broke my anterior maxillary bloody nose and chipped teeth,  goofball me makes me look tough like iâ’m in the army who knew that day at the ballpark would be but i learned one big lesson that day that even on the bad days good things come with a broken face and a dream i say on bad days there is things you can learn from if you fall then get back up you will rise and then you will be glad that you were down

title: Homeward Bound
author: ian
text: its been six months,  since i went away,  left with a tear in my eye,  but knew it had to be this way.   its almost the end,  of this struggle and fight,  because im coming back to you,   you're alomost in my sight,   god,  send me and angel,  and let me borrow her wings,  so i can go back to my people,  and feel like the king.   i've been given everything i dreamed of,  but it still didnt satisfy me,  i knew i had your love,  but its your presance i needed.   i knew i had to do this,  because i knew i had to realize,  how much your love means to me,  so much,  without it,  i would die.   god,  send me and angel,  from the heaven above,  and let her take me over the sea,  where it is just my family and me.

title: Share
author: ibtisam
text: i want to share my tears with you i want to share my love with you i want to share my happiness with you i want to share my strength with you my smiles , my loss, my good day, my bad day,  the rain, the sunshine,  hot coca, snowflakes. i want to share my life with you,  i always love you my love you are my world

title: Broken-Hearted Girl
author: icis
text: everyday i sit and wonder what life would have been if you were still here.  holding,  touching,  and kissing me and telling me how much you love me.  hearing those words made me feel so good inside. but now that you're gone i don't know what to do anymore or how i'm going to make it through another day.  so here i sit,  trying to find the missing pieces of my heart.

title: Study again?oh!

text: the big blue sky crowds round to wave,  nice beaming sun peeps in and smiles,  gentle bold breeze sweeps with a wink,  humming a soulful tune of hushy notes,  oh! how the leafy bunches dance to it! the dark little bird spells out the lyric,  aptly set in to the swing of those buds.  while ecstasy and nothing i could utter,  how in heavens with this bulky book do they await me to study 'n blabber?

title: This sunny  day

text: this sunny day, i pray   to the sun to shine the way home   for those who has lost it.  this sunny day, i pray to the heavens' to   ease the pain of all who lost someone   in this life time.  this sunny day,  i pray   for the rain to come and wash the    sorrow away from all of us.  this sunny day i pray,    for peace not only on earth,  but in   all our soul.

title: With in
author: imher
text: wish on a rainbow is all i can do.  dream of the good times that we never knew.  no late nights alone in your arms.  living in wonder,  thinking of you.  still looking for ways to uncover the truth.  you are so young is all they can say.  they don't know if i could change the way of the world i'd be your man.   two now walls have been built in between us.  too many dreams had been shattered around us.  if i seen to give up they still never win deep in my heart,  the strenght is with in.

title: Stuck in reality
author: inas
text: stuck in vicious days  between nightmares i lay  in ugly thoughts i live  take nothing but give  body has been exhausted   mind has been corrupted  try to improve  but nowhere i can fit and groove  usefulness is no more for me  tiresome prevented to set me free  maybe…if i slept in soil  where no one can join  there i can flee

title: Why me?
author: ingrid
text: a smart girl who got a beautiful smile,  who was always happy.  there comes a wind that wipes my smile and left tears.  every night crying myself to sleep.   peace,  happiness and love are impossible to me.  my soul is tired of paining all day.  my goals are now cooking,  cleaning and doing laundry.  my dreams and goals are crashed before they could even start.   i feel like i gambled with my own soul and lost everything.  i sold my dreams to strangers.  why it happened to me? why not that other girl? lot of why's are in my mind.   i also need so break from pain.  when will the rain come for me? people even forgot my beautiful smile,  because shame and sadness are now called my happiness.

title: The sweet feeling of deaph
author: irana
text: it feels like  lying down on a large garden of flowers,  on a silent of the wind blowing on your face,  feeling the breeze as a butterfly lays on a petal of a beautiful rose.   it is like the peaceful sensation of reading a book under a big tree,   but at the same time the mystery and loneliness of being blind lost in the middle of nowhere.

title: Iris Rain
author: iris
text: the smallest of things can make you smile because it is the little things are what matter the most. . .  you are so easy to talk to. . .  i have learnt to be happy from you. . .  you have also shown me how to always seen the best in everything. . .  it is because of you that i have peaceful days. . .  your message fill the words of my day. . .  because i don't seem to worry about things as much as i would do. . . all i need is to hear your voice before i end my day then it takes my stress away. . .  maybe this is the reason why i remember you every time from the moment i wake up till before i go to sleep. . .  always be careful gf. . .  ill just wait here. . .  ill get sleep now. . .  sorry for the trouble. . .

title: High School
author: isabella
text: you walk into this huge building not knowing what to find.  you enter small and eager then you leave grown and mature.  four years of your life pass you by in the blink of an eye.  you establish your reputation  and make your close friends but don't be surprised if they're not  there at the end.  senior year comes, it's finally here.  you do what you want  and you have no fear.  time flys by and you realize  it's almost over.   graduation day comes and they call  your name,  friends and family clap,  its all insane.  you go visit that building that was once so big.  that building full of everything,  everything you did.  those moments you'd be begging,  pleading for your time to come.  and look at now,  your time is done.

title: Old Days To Old Ways
author: isaiah
text: ah how i wish i was single again then i could talk with whomever i want back then i could flirt with whomever i care how i miss the laughs,  the smiles,  the joy ***** back then i was reknown for my talent and now my talents are forsaken my speech which i loved is now gallant now i am unfortunately taken ***** alas,  for it is not all bad as though i love my partner as i myself love she rises me up when i am so low as beautiful as a sweet morning dove ***** so even though i may miss the old days i would do no trade just for my old ways

title: The Happy Florist Monster
author: ishika
text: once there was a monster in a deep dark forest,  who wanted to be a pretty florist! arranging roses,  lilies and many a carnation,  it was his decoration station  he went to this mom and little brother dan,  and told them all about his plan,  his mother was confused and dan laughed,  dan said,  â“you will never master the craft!â”  head held high,  and skin gleaming blue,  â“iâ’ll do it! iâ’ll show you!â” and worked and arranged,  for days,  he was engaged  went to his mom and dan again,  took a pretty bouquet,  used his brain,  mom was happy and danâ’s jaw dropped,  the monster was so happy,  he hopped!  opened a tiny shop soon the street,  neither snow nor total heat,  could stop the little monster,  who had a dream,  just like you!

title: A Promise
author: ivan
text: why oh why do i always stick this needle in my eye? my selfish ways have given me a million goodbyes iâ’m so sick of myself,  iâ’m so sick of this hell all i need is to change,  why is it that in fear i dwell?  iâ’ve forgotten,  the love you all held for me my heart has rotten and i need a change of perspective please her beautiful eyes,  compliment her beautiful words,  that compliment her beautiful curves as the world spins,  we all wait for the worst,  why donâ’t we beak this curse?  youâ’ve seen me at my worst,  yet you loved me even when your heart felt like it would burst you held me in the storm,  even though i was the one that blew the horn and broke heavens gates you always believed in me even when i didnâ’t believe in you my selfish ways have always caused you pain,  and some days we all cry in vain  my heart torn open by the truth that has always held the key you are beautiful,  i wonder why i couldnâ’t see forgive me for thinking of only myself,  i now see you are worth more than diamonds yet so much more fragile

title: Water
author: jackie
text: water never sits there,  it's always on the go.  sometimes moving fast  or sometimes moving slow.  it takes its form in many ways in sleet or rain or snow.

title: Fall
author: jackie
text: when the temperature lowers,    and the leaves change,    that's when you know,    fall is approaching.    the sun won't be beating hot anymore,    and the pools won't be open,    summer will be long gone.    football games being played,    and bonfires happening,    all the stuff that make fall fun.    it's not my favorite time of the year,    i still can find many ways to enjoy it while it's here.

title: Apples
author: jaclyn
text: almost every afternoon,   i eat apples with a spoon.  every evening right at six,   i eat apples stacked on bricks.  as i get out of bed,  i eat apples with my head.  when i get feeling pretty sore,  i eat apples on the floor.   after i get all the i can pick,  i eat apples and get sick!

title: Summer Seasons
author: jacqueline
text: summer seasons dazzle women,  concrete moon gown must be delicious,  wine kicked fantasy of lust,  as slow circles swim around the heaving lake,  picture us singing sad songs that don't leave,  brother why are you so mad at the world?

title: Simple Love
author: jacqueline
text: a quick glance and a smile from each other without a word said whether from a distance or up close nothing ever needing to be said.  knowing what is meant with a blank expression from her face.  never trying to be something she wants to chase.  just the love for one another because we care for even the little things we dare to share.  because all what's said and done matters even if it may seem we do not care.  yet we know just from the look from in each others eyes that what we share will always and forever be there.
